title: fruit sauce
directions: Remove core and seeds from apples.
Remove seeds and membrane from oranges.
Grate apples and oranges with peeling.
Add sugar and mix well.
Chill.
Serve over plain cake.
Ad fresh, cool dessert in summertime.

title: a simple dessert
directions: Dip all but about 6 cookies in milk.
Place a layer of cookies on bottom of a square dish and top with cool whip and then a layer of cookies and another layer of cool whip.
Crush remaining 6 cookies and sprinkle on top.

title: war cake
directions: Boil water, brown sugar, white sugar, lard and raisins for 5 minutes and let cool.
Add eggs, baking powder or soda, cinnamon, allspice, ginger and salt.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel, quarter, boil and mash potatoes.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add to meat the onion, corn and taco seasoning and mix well.
Brown until onion is tender (may add water if needed).
In baking dish, place 1/2 of the mashed potatoes.
Put a layer of the corn and beef mixture on top.
Then place remaining potatoes on top of the corn and beef.
Place in a 350° oven until it starts to brown.
Take out and top with Cheddar cheese.
Place back in oven until cheese melts.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Melt butter, saute mushrooms and onions and remove from heat. Add everything else and put into a large casserole dish.
Bake, covered at 325° for 90 minutes.

title: broccoli newburg
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute celery in butter; stir in soup, sour cream and sherry.
Mix well and heat.
Do not boil.
Spoon sauce over broccoli.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice the first 4 ingredients thin.
Put in a dish; cover with salt and water.
Leave overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Add the vinegar, sugar, seed and pickle spices.
Put everything in pan; boil for 10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: broccoli in puff pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute mushrooms in butter over high heat until tender.
Set aside.

title: picante sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Grind or put through blender garlic, jalapenos and banana peppers (you may just chop).
Add tomatoes and cook until desired consistency.
Seal in glass sterilized jars.
For more heat, add more jalapenos.
Good with scrambled eggs.
Makes 7 or 8 pints.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Mix in blender the bananas, lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Add sugar mixture and freeze.
Stir every 2 to 3 hours. When ready to use, remove from freezer 3 hours before use.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
It should be slushy.

title: ruth's famous eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir in scalded milk slowly.
Cook in double boiler until mixture coats spoon. Cool.
Add salt to egg whites; beat stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla. Fold into custard mixture, then add whipped cream (optional).

title: dairy queen ice cream
directions: Soak gelatine in water.
Heat milk hot but not boiling. Remove from heat and add gelatine, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Cool and add milk and beaten eggs.

title: rockin' roller nibbles
directions: Puree bananas
in blender.
In a bowl, combine bananas, nuts, coconut, oats and sunflower seeds.	Spread evenly in a 9 x 15-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with oil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Stir to
separate;	bake for 10 minutes, stir again. Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: lemon daffodil dessert
directions: Combine juice, sugar and condensed milk.
Add whipping cream. Tear cake into small pieces and line the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over cake and mix together (just a little).
Chill for 24 hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10. Freezes well.
Great in summer.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix cake mix with 1 egg in pan with butter.
Spread out smoothly in pan to cover bottom of pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs thoroughly.
Pour over top of cake mix.
Bake at 340° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.
Serve in squares. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: juanita's chocolate icing or fudge
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; let boil 3 to 4 minutes, then beat with mixer until it thickens.
Add peanut butter and nuts.

title: beats me! chicken
directions: Place skinless chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: andrea's rocky road cookie bars
directions: Melt chips, milk and margarine in a double boiler.
In a large bowl, mix liquid, peanuts, and marshmallows.
Line a 9 x 13 inch pan with waxed paper, spread mixture in pan and chill for several hours.

title: kay crum's fudge
directions: Cook together 9 minutes (no longer), stirring constantly the first 4 ingredients. After the mixture starts to boil is when you start counting your 9 minutes.
After 9 minutes of boiling, set off stove eye and add large package of chocolate chips (or butterscotch, if desired).
Stir in well.
Add marshmallow cream, vanilla and at least 1 cup of chopped nuts (pecans, black walnuts or English walnuts).
Stir well and pour out on a buttered pan or paper.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Drain pineapple and combine with cottage cheese mixture. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover.
Shake hard.
Chill several hours.
Shake again just before serving.

title: chocolate custard pie
directions: Scald milk (set aside).
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and chocolate.
Pour hot milk slowly over egg mixture. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Custard is done when table knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Oven temperature:
450°. Bake 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes more.

title: punch
directions: Squeeze a little lime juice in the grapefruit-pineapple juice and
float	thin
slices of lime on top.
At last minute add the ginger ale and tie a clump of mint together and float in the punch.
This recipe for punch which has been reduced is suitable for
a child's party or any other small group.
It is so easy
to use quart size milk cartons to freeze the punch in and then you can just tear away the carton when ready to place them in the punch bowl.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add mashed bananas, vanilla and dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour in large loaf pan, greased and floured, and bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer until golden brown and toothpick, when inserted into middle, comes out clean.

title: raspberry brie tarts
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Place pastry shells on ungreased large cookie sheet. Cut cheese into 1/2-inch cubes. Place 3 cheese cubes into each fillo shell. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly. Remove partially baked shells from oven. Spoon 1/4 teaspoon spreadable fruit over cheese in each shell. Return to oven and bake an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until spreadable fruit is melted. Serve warm. Makes 30 appetizers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with tomato soup or for a new taste, top with bar-b-que sauce.

title: grandma's hot cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake in greased Pyrex dish or skillet at 375° for 1 hour.

title: play dough
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in medium pan.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Will turn into a ball.

title: lemon dijon baked fish
directions: Cut fillets in half and arrange in lightly greased pan.
Mix mustard, butter, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread mixture over fillet halves.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on fillet halves.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 2.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, cranberries, oranges, sugar and apple; let stand for 1/2 hour or so.
Add celery and pecans (grapes if you choose).
Mix and chill.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients (reserve 1/4 cup grated cheese) and pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 22 muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm and lightly golden brown.
In last 5 minutes of baking, you may put grated cheese on top.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil pasta until
firm,
rinse	and
drain.
Saute
the sausage and break up
into small pieces.
Mix with the drained spinach, drained cottage
cheese,
garlic, lemon juice, grated cheese, salt, pepper and
oregano.	Stir in beaten egg.
Stuff the shells with this mix
and
place in a greased baking dish. Top with tomato sauce.	Bake at
350° until all is hot and the cheese melted, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts with a little salt until done.
Shred or chop chicken.
Cook spaghetti.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9x13 baking dish sprayed lightly with Pam. Cook until bubbly (approximately 10-15 minutes) at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: leafy black cake
directions: Beat eggs; add shortening and milk.
Then add dry ingredients and hot water last.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until pick comes out clean.
Ice when cake is cool.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Using a 5-quart pot, cook beef in the chicken broth and water until tender. Skim off fat. Cut beef into small pieces and return to pot. Add bouillon cubes and pepper.
Add carrots, celery, onion and barley.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables and barley are tender. Makes 14 cups.

title: macaroni skillet
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes.
Stir in bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, mushrooms with liquid and macaroni.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is tender and most of liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: jello salad(especially good with ham)
directions: Dissolve lime jello and lemon jello into 4 cups of hot water. Add pineapple chunks, marshmallows and pecans.
Cook together until thick the egg, flour, sugar and pineapple juice. Mix with jello mixture. Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: honey bun ring
directions: Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter and the honey into the bottom of a greased 5-cup ring mold.
Place biscuits around the ring, overlapping slightly.
Pour remaining melted butter over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Turn onto a plate; serve warm.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake cake; let cool.

title: dinosaur food
directions: Mix dirt and swamp water; add crushed bone and fat.
Bring mixture to a boil for 1 minute.
Add dried grass and squashed bugs.
Cool.
Drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls.
Eat and enjoy.

title: white salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Combine with almonds and marshmallows.
Mix with
whipped
cream
and
mayonnaise.
Add pinch of salt and a
little
sugar	to taste.
Let stand overnight.	If it absorbs all the dressing add a little more cream before serving.

title: salsa(large quantities for bottling)
directions: Cut tomatoes in chunks for chunky salsa or place them in blender for smooth salsa.
Mix all ingredients and cook together until desired thickness.
Pack in pint bottles and pressure cook at 10 pounds for 20 minutes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Melt together the Velveeta cheese and margarine.
Mix the first and second mixtures together and pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot spinach salad with almonds
directions: Heat
oven
Spread almonds on a baking sheet and toast
in
the
oven until golden, about 10 minutes.
Let cool. Pull
stems
from
the
spinach
and
wash leaves.	Put spinach in	a salad bowl with the raisins and almonds.
Bring vinegar, 1/2
teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper to a boil in
a small saucepan.
Add oil and heat.
Pour the warm dressing
over spinach, toss and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces (do not use stems).
Add onion, cheese and bacon.
In bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli and mix together.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: *More nuts may be used, if desired.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Stir 1/2 cup of salt into first four ingredients and cover with ice cubes.
Soak for about 3 hours.
Remove cucumbers and mix from salt water and drain.
Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients and then add cucumber mixture to hot vinegar.
Heat to hot but not boiling.
Mixture will change colors.
Pack into jars and seal.
Do Not Overcook.

title: shepherd's sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together mutton, breadcrumbs, salt and pepper. Place in a 9-inch pie plate and pat with fingers to line bottom and sides, like a pie crust.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, cream and eggs, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into prepared meat crust, dot top with butter and dust with nutmeg.
Bake until knife blade inserted into center comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Buy frozen rolls and let thaw.
Roll into circles.
Melt butter and add powdered garlic to taste; spread on rolls.
Crumble sausage in frying pan; cook until brown, then drain.
Crumble fine and sprinkle sausage on rolls.
Roll the circles up; pinch ends and let rise.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Add 1 can milk to corn, eggs and cornstarch. Season to taste. Bake in a cool
325° to 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: crab cakes
directions: Makes around 60 crab cakes.

title: chicken with lemon-caper cream
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add shallots, saute for 1 minute.
Raise heat and add chicken.
Saute until they are lightly browned.
Add lemon juice, stir and scrape bottom of pan with wooden spoon to remove lumps or brown bits.
When most of lemon juice has evaporated, add cream.
Gently boil until thick, 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir in capers and serve over hot pasta. Garnish with parsley.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Cut steaks into 6 serving pieces.
Dredge in flour mixed with salt and pepper to taste; place in crock-pot.
Add chopped vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour tomatoes over meat and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 10 hours.

title: grandma addie's tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan. Cream sugar and shortening.
Combine soup with water and soda. Add to first mixture, alternating with dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Check for doneness with clean toothpick.
Frost with cream cheese frosting:

title: charcoal grilled steak
directions: Place steaks in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over steaks, coating all sides.
Marinate several hours in refrigerator, turning once.
Place on grill and sear on both sides.
Raise grill to about 5 inches from coals. Cook 15 minutes, turning once, or until desired degree of doneness is reached.

title: festive marshmallow salad
directions: Mix the sour cream and cottage cheese.
Mix in fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges.
Mix in the package of marshmallows.
Take the maraschino cherries, cut them in half and mix throughout. Finally, take the maraschino cherry juice and add about 1/2 to the salad.
This will give it a nice, pink look.
Chill several hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook ground chuck with salt and onion.
When brown, drain on paper towel.
In a large bowl, mix soup and Veg-All.
Add meat mixture.
Pour in crust.
Put other crust on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Great with a salad.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: *Reduce sugar to 2/3 cup if using frozen strawberries.

title: crispy pita snacks
directions: Mix ingredients and brush on ripped up pita bread.
Bake at 325° until crispy.

title: chicken noodle delight casserole
directions: Boil or broil chicken until fully-cooked.
Then shred chicken. Boil Ramen noodles.
Chop green pepper and onion; add margarine and milk.
Place in oven dish and cook for 15 minutes, then add Cheddar cheese on top and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Bring vinegar mixture to boil with squash and onions.
Place in jars and seal.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar and cream. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add vanilla. Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 80 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let cool 5 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Put all ingredients together in saucepan, except vanilla and pecans.
Stir only until the sugars are dissolved.
Cook to a soft ball stage (about 235°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecans and stir just until it starts to get firm (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Drop on waxed paper or into cupcake papers.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, salt
and
pepper
in a small bowl;
set aside. Combine eggs, 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and water; mix well. Clean mushrooms
with
damp
paper
towels;
dredge
in flour mixture and dip in egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Chill at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix jello in boiling water; add sugar, lemon and pineapple mix.
Let set in refrigerator until cold.
When cold, fold in 1 package Dream Whip, already whipped.
Pinch small pieces of cake. Put mixture in a large round bowl.
Later, place bowl of mixture in warm water to loosen from sides.
Turn onto plate; top with other Dream Whip, whipped.
Spread on cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: bow tie and beef stir-fry
directions: Cut steak in strips (2-inches); set aside.
In large skillet or wok, add 1 cup of the beef broth, asparagus and onion.
Cook until asparagus is tender.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Cook steak.
Add salt and pepper.
Add asparagus and onion to steak. Add rest of broth and tomato puree.
Stir until blended.
Add in cooked bow ties and heat until hot.
Serve with fresh grated Parmesan cheese on top.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Take chicken off bone. Add salt and pepper to broth.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream until fluffy. Add melted chocolate, then unbeaten eggs.
Beat until light.
Sift flour and measure; add baking powder, salt and soda.
Sift twice more.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beating between additions.
Add boiling water and vanilla and beat well.
Bake in 2 greased (or sprayed) 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool; frost with Fudge Frosting.

title: good morning muffins
directions: Place melted butter in a microwave-safe measuring cup.
Crack egg open and pour into measuring cup with melted butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Microwave on High 45 seconds.
Place half of English muffin on microwave-safe plate.
Place cooked egg on top of English muffin.
Place cheese slice on top of egg.
Microwave on High 15 to 20 seconds or until cheese starts to melt.
Place other half of English muffin on top and eat.

title: green  beans and oil
directions: Add crushed garlic to oil poured into a 2 qt. pan.
Add onion and cook for 5 mins.
Add green beans and mix well.
Cover and let simmer.
till beans are done.

title: beef stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown in butter.
Add garlic (minced) and onion (sliced).
Add mushrooms.
Cook until onions are tender.

title: rugen'rad salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Preheat the grill. Place the walnuts on a baking sheet and bake until golden brown, being careful not to burn, for 5 to 6 minutes. Remove the nuts from the pan and transfer them to a mixing bowl. Toss the walnuts with the vinegar. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside and cool. Cut the radicchio into fourths. Season with olive oil, salt and pepper. Grill for 2 minutes on each side. Remove and cool. With a sharp knife, julienne the lettuce.
Whisk the walnut oil into the walnut mixture. Season the dressing to taste with the honey.

title: hot deviled potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions (make on the dry side).
Heat sour cream (do not boil).
Add mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt and sugar; stir to blend.
Mix into hot potatoes with onion.
Immediately turn into 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Heat in a 350° oven about 10 minutes. Makes 5 servings.

title: best peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, butter, salt and milk in a heavy pan.
Cook to soft ball stage (234° to 238°) not too high or it will burn. 238° is better to insure a good set.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and pour into a buttered 9-inch pan.
You can put pecan halves on top of each piece.
Allow to set completely before cutting.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Mix
sugar and flour; add slightly beaten eggs, pecans, butterscotch
chips, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake
1 hour at 325° until lightly browned.
Serve with whipped
cream or Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Do not refrigerate after it is made or leftover.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Cook chopped broccoli and drain.
Add to mixtures.
Add rice.
Season to taste.
Add diced, cooked chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
If desired, add 1 can onion rings to top and bake awhile longer.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Mix liquids and add to dry mixture.
Form balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Chill in container.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine all filling ingredients and pour into pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: polish poczki
directions: Dissolve yeast in luke warm milk.
Add 2 cups flour; let stand in a warm place about 1/2 hour.
Then beat eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt till light.
Add mixture to yeast mixture; add 5 cups flour cover and allow to rise for 1 hour or till double.
Turn on floured dough and pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with round doughnut cutter.
Cover and let rise again till double and light. Fry in deep fat at 375° till done on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
When cool cut 1/2 way through and fill with jelly and sprinkle with powder sugar.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown roast and onions.
Add roast and onions to pot with coffee and water.
Cook until meat is tender and pulls apart.
(I use pressure cooker.)
Combine remaining ingredients and add to pulled apart meat.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Melt margarine, cream and sugar in bowl.
Add egg.
Add yeast to cream mixture.
Add flour.
Stir until well mixed.
Place in airtight bowl.
Place in refrigerator. Drop by spoonfuls in greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pans and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: kidney bean and biscuit casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef; remove and set aside.
Add bacon and cook until crisp; remove from skillet.
Crumble and add to beef.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add onion, green pepper, celery and garlic to skillet and saute until tender. Drain beans, reserving 1 cup liquid (or add enough water to liquid to equal 1 cup).
Combine beans, reserved liquid, beef, vegetables, tomato sauce, chili powder, mustard and salt; mix well.
Spoon onto casserole, making 6 biscuits.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cookie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg.
Pat into baking dish and sprinkle with pecans.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs. Pour over other mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°, until brown.

title: chin chin pastry(nigerian)
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add one egg at a time.
Add flour, nutmeg, salt and liquid (water or milk).
Blend until mixture is stiff and fluffy (like pizza dough).
Roll with a rolling pin to flatten.
Cut the pastry into cube or diamond shape.
Place in pan with hot oil and deep fry.
Store in a dry container with a tight lid.
Use as snacks for 20 or more people.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine macaroni, butter, cheese and seasonings.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine eggs; add milk.
Pour over macaroni.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: dobi
directions: Mix until consistency of mayonnaise.
Keep in refrigerator. Lightly smooth on baking pans.

title: shirley's sweet trash
directions: Nice after school snack. Tuna salad with your choice of ingredients.
Brown or toast rye bread. Top with tuna.
Add a slice of tomato, if you like. Top with cheese and melt.
Serve open-face.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients one minute after it comes to a boil. Add other ingredients after you remove from fire.
Pour into a long 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 32 cookies.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Let set in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into mold. Put in refrigerator until set.

title: icicle pickles(3 days)
directions: First Day:
Take cucumber sticks made from large cucumbers (cut out seeds).
Soak sticks in lime water for 24 hours.
Use 2 cups lime to 2 gallons water.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients approximately 15 minutes (until vegetables are cooked).
Heat oleo and flour until smooth.
Add milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Add to vegetable mixture; cover and simmer on low approximately 15 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, cook garlic in margarine for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Before serving, stir in a little Tabasco sauce, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Combine sugars, oleo, oil, egg and vanilla in a large bowl; mix well.
Add flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into small balls, or drop by spoon onto cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick-easy lemon icebox pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all except graham cracker crusts.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.
May top with cherry pie filling (if like).

title: cheese luncheon dish
directions: Beat eggs;
add milk and remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie baking dish and cook in moderate 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until brown and set.

title: spicy potpourri
directions: Mix all together.
Use as you would potpourri, in sachets, bowls, centerpieces, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pinch chicken off of bone.
Mix with other ingredients and put in dish.
Pour dry stuffing mix into bowl.
Melt 1 stick of butter; pour over stuffing and mix well.
Pour this over other mixture. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: basic roll dough
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm, stirring constantly until shortening almost melts.
Add to dry mixture.
Add egg.
Beat at low speed with mixer for 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough. Shape into ball.
Place in lightly greased bowl.
Turn once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down, turn on floured surface.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread about 1 cup sauce, arrange a layer of uncooked lasagna, top with some sauce (being sure to cover pasta entirely), Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat, gently pressing lasagna pieces into cheese mixture. End with a final layer of lasagna.
Pour remaining sauce over, making sure all lasagna pieces are covered.
Top with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes until lightly browned.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to a boil the crushed pineapple and 1/4 cup sugar. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin, then cream cheese.
Add ice water.
Stir and let chill until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip, then chill.

title: butter crunch crust
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients with hands.
Spread dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
(Watch carefully so crust doesn't burn or brown.)
Take from oven and stir with spoon.
Save 3/4 cup for topping.
Immediately press the remaining mixture against the bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan. Cool.
Pour in your favorite cream filling.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chill 1 hour.
Scrumptious with lemon chiffon filling.

title: strawberry lovers' pie
directions: In a saucepan, melt 2 ounces chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Spread or brush over the bottom and up the sides of pastry shell.
Chill.

title: hamburger steak casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, line the ground beef patties on the bottom; peel and slice the potatoes.
Salt and pepper over all. Chop
up the onion; pour on top of the potatoes.
Mix the soup and water.
Pour over the onions.
Cover with foil and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave cheese sticks
directions: Cut
bacon strips lengthwise; wrap around bread sticks, roll in
cheese.
Place
on and cover with paper towels.
Cook on High 5 to 6 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: no cholesterol salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients in a shaker.
Sprinkle in lemon pepper and shake until mixed.

title: simple sesame cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, still beating, until light and fluffy.
Add flour; mix until just combined.
Stir in sesame, coconut and pecans.
Chill.
Make balls and flatten with fork. Bake at 350°.

title: cornbread-bacon dressing
directions: Heat margarine in heavy skillet over low heat; add bacon, onion, celery and seasonings and saute until tender.
Combine with cornbread and white bread in bowl.
Mix thoroughly and stuff loosely in turkey.
Yields enough for 10 pound turkey.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Combine apple filling, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add nuts. Spread 1/2 in pie shell.
Chill remaining apple mixture.
Pour milk and cream in small bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon over apple mix in pie shell.
Freeze 1 hour or chill 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with reserved apple mixture and additional whipped topping if desired.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix soups together and pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bone chicken and place on top of soups.
Use reserved chicken liquid to mix dressings.
Spoon over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crispy onion rings
directions: Peel onions; cut into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings. Combine next 8 ingredients and egg yolks; beat well.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Dip onion rings into batter; fry in deep hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Use beater to smooth cream cheese, milk and vanilla together. Add lemon juice and stir until completely blended.
Divide equally into 2 crusts.
Top with strawberry pie filling (can also use blueberry or cherry).
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mexican spiced hot cocoa
directions: In a large mug, stir together first 4 ingredients. Add the boiling water and stir.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, stirring until mixture is blended.
Turn into greased, 9-inch pan. Spread dough evenly.
Top with melted butter.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: In baking dish, place all ingredients except meat and stir. Add meat and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: eggless sugar-free strawberry ice cream
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; cool.
Mix all ingredients together, except 2% milk, and pour into freezer can.
Fill with milk to fill line of can.
Freeze.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Use a teflon cookie sheet with sides (a jelly roll pan). Grease and flour pan lightly.
Heat to boiling butter, cocoa and water.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Beat in 2 eggs and add buttermilk, vanilla, soda and vinegar.
Next, mix in sugar, flour and salt until well blended.
Pour into pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check after 15 minutes.

title: pan roasted chicken with garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium size baking pan, mix the garlic, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, water, 1/2 of the oregano, melted butter, pepper and cayenne.
Cross hatch smooth side of chicken breast with 1/4-inch deep cuts.
Place chicken, scored side down, in pan.

Spoon sauce over chicken to coat. Bake chicken, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Stir remaining oregano into sauce. Serve chicken, scored side up, and with a tablespoon of sauce poured over top of each. Serve with loaf of warm French bread and rice pilaf.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, mandarin oranges and Cool Whip; then add cooled jello liquid.
Now pour the ingredients into a large Tupperware dish with an 8 to 12-cup capacity and chill overnight.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, cream and vanilla to soft ball stage.
Pour over 4 quarts popped corn.
Form into balls.

title: salad dressing cake 2
directions: Combine all ingredients as written. Beat well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
"Delicious."

title: ms. josie's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Make 3 rolls the length of wax paper. Keep in refrigerator.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: rutabaga salad
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Drain and rinse. Peel rutabaga and shred medium to fine.
Add remaining ingredients and toss with enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Chill. Keeps well.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces and salt.
Sprinkle chicken with garlic.
Combine oregano, lemon peel and juice and water and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Continue to bake.
Baste with drippings once or twice. Bake for about 40 minutes or until fork-tender.
Pan drippings can be used over rice.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Make
corn
bread according to box directions.
Crumble half of
corn
bread
in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Layer vegetables and bacon in order, saving enough bacon to go on top. Mix
mayonnaise,
sugar and salad pickles.
Spread on top of casserole.
Add remaining half of corn bread; sprinkle with bacon. Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on box.
Brown ground meat.
Strain off fat.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Check at 40 minutes. Test with toothpick. Makes 8 small loaf pans.

title: broccoli with red pepper and shallots(diabetic)
directions: Bring 2 quarts of lightly salted water to a boil in a large sauce pan over high heat.
Add broccoli;
boil uncovered 3 to 5 minutes, or until bright green and tender.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Drain well.
Melt margarine in 12 inch nonstick skillet, over medium heat.
Add bell pepper and shallots.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place in a serving dish.
Garnish with a toasted and salted almonds if desired.
Yields 12 cups.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Stir well.
Chill before serving.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring milk and margarine to boil over medium heat.
Add flour all at once, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a ball and leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring mixture until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until puffed golden brown.
Wrap and freeze.
Heat in oven before serving.

title: chocolate yummies
directions: Coat a 13 x 9 x 2-inch microwave dish with cooking spray. Place 6 whole pieces graham crackers on bottom of dish; fit remaining pieces to cover bottom of pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows over crackers. Microwave on High 1 minute or until they are puffy. Remove from microwave and cool.

title: surprise-crust pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a 12-inch round pizza pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In bowl, mix rice, Parmesan cheese and egg together until thoroughly combined.
Press rice mixture firmly into prepared pizza pan to form a "crust".
Bake 20 minutes. Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add onion and pepper slices and cook, stirring frequently, until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except half the onion rings.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
If using frozen onion rings, top casserole with them now.
If using Durkee's, do not add to top until nearly finished baking (5 minutes).
Bake casserole (uncovered) at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: never fail blueberry pie
directions: Mix in blender 1 cup blueberries and water.
In saucepan, mix sugar and cornstarch, then add salt and blueberry/water mix.
Heat until thick.
Add butter and remaining berries.
Put in unbaked pie shell and add top crust (9-inch).
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.
Cool.
It will not run when cut.

title: orange butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add yolks.
Add combined baking powder and flour, also juice and rind of orange.
Roll out dough and cut with fancy round 2-inch cookie cutter.
Half of these are to be baked as cut; the other half should have a hole cut in the center with a thimble before baking.
These are the tops.
When cooled, put together with currant jelly.
For baking, use oven at 350° and bake for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat well the egg, buttermilk or sour milk and soda.
Beat in remainder of ingredients.
Beat for 1 minute.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in blender and then add enough ice to fill to the top line of the blender.
Blend on high speed.

title: fast fiesta shepard's pie
directions: Cook beef in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Stir in tomato soup, corn, picante sauce and cumin. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes. Mix cheese soup, milk and butter in saucepan. Heat to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in potato flakes. Let stand 30 seconds. Mix with fork until evenly moistened. Drop potatoes by large spoonfuls onto beef mixture.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Bake cake according to package, adding 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, pour on all of Hershey's syrup or fudge topping.
Cool.
When cake is cool, mix 2 tablespoons creme de menthe with the Cool Whip.
Spread on cake. Refrigerate leftover cake.

title: spezziello fruit salad(good for potluck or a lot of company.)
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water 10 minutes; drain and rinse. Mix together and cook juices, flour and salt until thick; add egg and cook a little longer.
Combine cooked mixture with noodles; refrigerate overnight.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Drain asparagus and reserve 1 cup liquid.
Heat liquid and dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Pour gelatin mixture into hot liquid and stir. Fold in mayonnaise, whipped cream, salt and lemon juice. Add chopped asparagus and almonds.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: conway twitty's three-bean salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, Dr. Pepper, salt and pepper in jar with tight-fitting lid.
Shake vigorously.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Place onion rings, green beans, wax beans and kidney beans in salad bowl; toss well.
Pour dressing over vegetables; toss lightly.
Chill, tightly covered, for several hours to overnight, tossing occasionally.
Toss well just before serving.

title: herbed oyster crackers
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients and stir through crackers.
Spread on two cookie sheets.
Bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg and sugar; add milk, flour and vegetable oil.
Mix well; add blueberries and mix very lightly.
Fill greased muffin cups 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: grilled jalapeno peppers
directions: Slice jalapenos lengthwise; stuff with cream cheese. Wrap with bacon and wrap in foil. Place on grill until bacon is done.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Layer from beans on bottom to olives on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: potato wedges
directions: Preheat
oven
to
In
a small saucepan over low heat, melt
butter; stir in catsup, mustard, paprika and salt until well
mixed.
Cut each potato into 4 wedges; slash each wedge crosswise at 1/4 inch intervals, but do not cut through skin. Place
potatoes, skin side down, on cookie sheet; brush potatoes with
1/3 of butter mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
(Brush potatoes occasionally with remaining
butter
mixture during baking.) Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican enchiladas casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add soups and enchilada sauce. Alternate tortillas and meat sauce.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chicken tenders
directions: Cut breasts into strips.
Mix flour, parsley, oregano and seasoned salt.
Coat strips in flour mixture; fry in oleo until golden brown.

title: laura's hamburg pie
directions: Brown hamburg, onions, mushrooms.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts and butter; mix thoroughly and press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
In medium bowl with electric mixer, combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 carton of the dessert topping.
Beat until well combined and spread over cooled cake layer in dish.
Refrigerate.

title: mother's soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Chop onions.
Add potatoes, onions and stewed tomatoes to the water.
Boil until potatoes are tender. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add macaroni and boil 5 minutes. Turn burner off.
Cover.
Macaroni will soften and soup will be ready in about 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in cooking oil in skillet until soft.
Combine all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover.
Cook on low 3 to 4 hours. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: old rose punch
directions: Combine the pineapple juice, pina colada mixer, sugar, tropical punch and grape juice.
Mix well.
Freeze.
About 2 hours before serving, remove from freezer and allow to thaw slightly. Using a knife, make a slush out of the punch and add 7-Up or Sprite, as needed.
Makes about 2 1/2 gallons (without the 7-Up). Will serve 100.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into meatballs.
Brown in butter.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Dilute the milk with equal amount of water and scald.
Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch or flour.
Add scalded milk and cook over hot water until thick.
Cool.
Add vanilla.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Pour in two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° until firm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, margarine, salt and vanilla. Mix well and place in a well-buttered casserole.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Add the corn, pimento, carrots and onions.
Toss to blend.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken with chipped beef
directions: Place chipped beef (no salt) crumbled in bottom of buttered casserole (7 x 11-inch).
Wrap bacon around the chicken breasts and sprinkle with pepper. Combine soup, sour cream and cream cheese in a blender or electric mixer.
Add mushrooms with spoon and pour over chicken breasts in casserole.
Cover with foil and cook at 300° for 2 hours.
Remove foil and add Sauterne.
Cook for one more hour.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: mushroom cream soup with brie croutons
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add onions, leeks and mushrooms. Cook until tender, 5 minutes.
Add sherry and bay leaf until reduced to a little bit of liquid.
Add stock, cook until mushrooms are tender.
Add cream, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook gently until reduced.
At serving time, remove bay leaf.
Ladle soup into individual crocks (heatproof).
Spread bread slices with Brie and place over top of soup.
Place under broiler until browned.
Serve hot!

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 25 minutes).

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange alternately in layers in casserole, saving some cheese and all cracker crumbs for topping. Cook with cover on casserole for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat together in a bowl, the egg white and water.
Pour in the pecans and using a wooden spoon, stir until all pecans are coated. Sift together the sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Stir pecans in mixture until they are well coated.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Store in a cake tin or glass jar.

title: texas eggs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in large, flat casserole. Combine next 3 ingredients and layer on top of egg mixture.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Spread cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: new year's wheat dish(amen masiouk)
directions: Place rinsed whole wheat in 4 quarts water.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat and cook until tender.
Cool.
Add sugar, walnuts and raisins.
Mix well.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Make a dressing from the last 5 ingredients and combine the two together.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with paprika and serve on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: president ike's cake(over 50 years old - 1940)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Dissolve cocoa in boiling water.
Mix until smooth.
Cool.
Add egg yolks and vanilla to sugar and butter mixture well.
Add cooled cocoa solution.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Have sour milk at room temperature.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk in thirds. Beat until smooth after each addition.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: harry's fluffy hush puppies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix in enough buttermilk to make to cornbread consistency.
Let stand in refrigerator 4 hours before cooking.
Deep fry in hot oil.

title: fiesta bean soup
directions: Brown onion with beef.
Put everything in pot and cook for 1 to 1-1/2 hours on low.
Recipe doubles easily, and is easy to freeze leftovers.

title: cajun country casserole
directions: Melt the cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter in double boiler.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet and saute shrimp until they turn pink, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and continue to saute until wilted.
Add melted cream cheese, butter and soup.
Mix well.
Add pimentos, seasonings, crabmeat and rice.
Mix well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole. Top with bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly. Garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley.
Serves 8.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil margarine, brown sugar, Karo syrup, salt, vanilla and soda for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour at once over popped corn and peanuts (optional) on large cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread apart and cool.
Store in tight container.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and smoked salmon until well blended.
Add onion or chives plus lime juice.
Place in small bowl or form into ball.
Refrigerate 1 hour or longer.

title: garrett's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter and egg. Stir in flour; blend together well.
Chill dough.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour and crisscross.
Bake until set, but not hard, at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: breakfast tacos
directions: Brown sausage in pan; drain.
Add hash browns, peppers, onion, celery and eggs.
Mix.
Butter a large 13 x 9-inch or larger casserole or spray with nonstick spray.
Place mixture in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese and heat until melted.

title: sherried mushrooms and broccoli vermicelli
directions: In a large skillet, heat the oil.
Add the garlic and plum or cherry tomatoes.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes, or until the tomatoes collapse.
Add the canned tomatoes, water, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp cheese ring
directions: Blend well.
Spread around shallow glass dish (as for pie crust).
Mix 1/2 cup pickle relish and 1 cup chili sauce together; spread over cheese mixture.
Place cooked shrimp over top; chill. May use crab meat or a combination of shrimp and crab meat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix sour cream sauce mix and milk; let stand 10 minutes.
Add cream cheese and half of the shredded dried beef to sour cream mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape into a ball and roll ball in remaining dried beef.
Serve on snack crackers.

title: everlasting play dough
directions: Get a pint size jar.
Put bacon grease and a chunk of banana at the bottom.
Smear vaseline 3/4-inch around the inside rim and 1/2-inch from the top.
Two traps can take care of a four room apartment.
Seal the jars and trash the roaches.
This really works.

title: no-fuss lasagne
directions: In a large saucepan, brown beef; drain.
Add tomato paste, water, spaghetti sauce mix, sugar, parsley, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a bowl, mix eggs and cottage cheese, 1/2 of the Cheddar and 1/2 of the Mozzarella; set aside.
Spoon 1/3 meat sauce into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place 1/2 of the uncooked noodles on top.
Pour on 1/3 meat sauce and press down.
Spoon cottage cheese mixture over all.
Cover with rest of noodles and meat sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover, sprinkle on remaining cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: veggie chili
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the peppers and onion and heat until they soften. Add remaining ingredients. Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat. Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan pie 2
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup and nuts. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits; add other ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes in casserole dish in a 350° oven (spray casserole dish with Pam).

title: scalloped corn and broccoli
directions: Saut onion in margarine until soft.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add milk and cook, stirring until thick.

title: hot jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Mix cheeses and put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Spread chopped peppers over cheese, then top off with remaining cheese.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top bubbles and edges brown slightly.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: taco surprise
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on serving plate or tray.
Layer on cream cheese the other ingredients in order.
Arrange tostado chips around edge of tray.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in a large greased iron skillet at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Press crescent rolls flat on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until golden brown. Let cool. Mix dry Ranch dressing, cream cheese and mayonnaise together. Spread on top of crescent rolls. Sprinkle vegetables and cheese over top and refrigerate.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Mix first 5 ingredients together in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed.
Combine salt, flour, baking powder, and baking soda, and add gradually to butter mixture.
Stir in sour cream. Alternately layer mixture #1 and mixture #2 in tube pan, starting with mixture #1.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine ground cranberries and sugar.
Dissolve the jello in water and chill until set.
Add it to the cranberries, ground orange and nuts and stir well.
Pour into mold and chill overnight.
Or, just put in a bowl and serve like a jam.

title: raisin sauce(for ham)
directions: Cook - stirring until clear.
Serve on hot ham slices.

title: walnut meringue pie
directions: Beat sugar into egg whites.
Fold in crushed graham squares, baking powder, walnuts and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9-inch buttered pie pan.
Serve cool with Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Add syrup, vanilla and nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine beef, flour, salt, marjoram and pepper in a 3-quart casserole.
Stir to coat.
Dissolve bouillon granules in hot water.
Add to meat; cover.
Microwave at High for 10 minutes; stir.
Reduce power to Low.
Microwave for 30 minutes.
Stir in the vegetables; re-cover.
Microwave at Low for 45 to 60 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender, stirring 2 times.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: steamed or boiled baby red potatoes and carrots
directions: You will need steamer insert for a 2-quart covered pan or just the 2-quart covered saucepan.

title: tiny tofu cheesecakes
directions: Place tofu on paper towel and gently squeeze out excess moisture.
Crumble and place in blender along with cream cheese, egg, sugar and almond extract.
Whirl until smooth and creamy.

title: filet mignon with horseradish gravy(an easy elegant dish)
directions: Prepare gravy according to package directions; stir in horseradish and mushrooms.
Set aside.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually. Beat egg yolks and add to butter and sugar. Add molasses. Sift flour, baking powder and nutmeg together; add to egg mixture alternately with grape juice. Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Chop nuts, raisins and orange peel, flouring with 4 tablespoons of flour. Stir into mixture; do not beat. Pour into a tube pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake for 3 hours at 250°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle half the can of onion rings on top.
Mix soup and milk together until smooth.
Pour over the green beans.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and then with the remaining onion rings.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican sandwiches
directions: Brown the meat and drain.
Add beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, onion and chili peppers.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Make cornbread and cut into squares.
Slice each piece open and spread the mixture over the cornbread.
Add a slice of cheese and allow to melt.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered jar.
Refrigerate; shake before using.

title: white chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken stock (broth). Reserve 1 c. for later.
Drain spaghetti. Combine cheese, soup, milk and 1 c. of reserved stock until cheese is melted. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix chicken, broccoli, spaghetti and sauce together.
Put in casserole and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cake frosting
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple and let stand for 5 minutes.
Then add Cool Whip and mix.
Use what you need of the frosting and put the rest in freezer for the next time.

title: spicy jalapeo-shrimp pasta
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen. Peel and devein shrimp. Cook linguine according to package directions. Chop jalapeos finely. In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add jalapeos, garlic, salt and pepper; cook and stir for 1 minute. Add shrimp; cook and stir about 3 minutes more or until shrimp turn opaque. Stir in tomatoes; heat through. Drain linguine; toss with shrimp mixture. If you would like, top with Parmesan cheese.

title: spray n wash
directions: Blend equal parts of liquid detergent, ammonia and water. Blend and pour into spray bottle and keep in laundry room. Comparable to any Spray And Wash you can purchase.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef
and
onion.
Drain off fat, if necessary.
Add
remaining
ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts. Serve with corn chips or chips of your choice.

title: pumpkin chews(cookies)
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix in oats and set aside.
Combine sugars, shortening and spices, blending well.
Beat in egg.
Gradually mix in flour-oat mixture alternately with pumpkin.
Stir in chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix together well all of the ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Will freeze very well.
Yields 10 servings.

title: apple pinwheels
directions: Core apple; stuff inside with peanut butter, cream cheese or cheese spread.
Chill.
Serve crosswise and serve.
Great kids' snack.

title: italian sausage tortellini soup
directions: Saute sausage 10 minutes in Dutch oven until crumbled and cooked through.
Transfer to large bowl with slotted spoon.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of fat.
Add onion and garlic to pan. Saute until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Return sausage to pan. Add stock, tomatoes, tomato sauce, zucchini, carrot, pepper, wine, basil and oregano.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, about 40 minutes.
Add tortellini to soup and cook until tender about 8 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve in bowls and sprinkle with cheese.

title: roast rabbit
directions: Wash and dry rabbit; melt margarine and brown rabbit.
Add salt and pepper, prunes and wine.
Cover pan and place in oven at 350° for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Check every 1/2 hour and turn pieces; add water if needed.

title: pretzel pepper dip
directions: Beat cheese, butter, Ranch dressing and pepper until smooth. Spread in shallow serving dish and cover top with cracked pepper. Serve with pretzel knots. Will keep in refrigerator for a long time.

title: chocolate party mix
directions: In a small pot, melt butter, peanut butter and mint semi-sweet morsels.
Add vanilla to mixture.
Pour over cereal and pretzels. Mix and cool a little.
Shake into package of powdered sugar.
Add M&M's peanut candy.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil onion and zucchini 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Mix with zucchini and onion.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Place pork chops in pan in a single layer.
No need to brown chops.
Spoon undiluted soup over chops to cover.
Sprinkle with onion rings.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: grandma wamsley's gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Stir in flour, spices and soda, alternating with boiling water.
Pour into floured pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; stir in egg.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix in raisins and oats.
Beat well.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: french onion soup(famous barr)
directions: Slice onions 1/8-inch thick.
Melt butter, place onions in it and saute slowly for 1 1/2 hours in a large soup pot.
Add all other ingredients, except bouillon; saute over low heat 10 minutes more.
Add bouillon; simmer for 2 hours.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend the cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add the next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles; roll out to make twelve 3-inch squares.
Place chicken mixture (approximately 2 tablespoons) on squares.
Bring up sides and twist with melted butter.
Sprinkle croutons on top.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until brown.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crumble the Oreo cookies in bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.

title: woodsman's soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat all ingredients to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 10 (1 cup) servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except sherbet.
Add sherbet to punch bowl when ready to serve.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Grease a large baking dish.
Cut bread into 3/4 to 1-inch thick slices.
Arrange in one layer in dish.

title: mike's crab and corn chowder
directions: Saute green onions and garlic in butter or margarine until tender.
Add Pork and Veal Magic.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Serve with hot French bread.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix the Kool-Aid with sugar.
Add 2 quarts water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add grapefruit or pineapple juice.
Chill before serving.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Combine the ground meat, bread crumbs, egg, parsley, minced garlic and salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix well and form into tiny meatballs. Place meatballs on a baking sheet and bake for about 25 minutes at 350 degrees, until brown.
About 10 minutes before serving, bring the chicken broth to a boil and add the spinach to cook until tender.
Add the meatballs and return to a simmer. Stir in the romano cheese and serve.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Make sure sweet potatoes are firmly baked before adding topping.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Work flour, vanilla and nuts into creamed mixture.
Form into small balls.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet in a moderate oven (325° to 375°) for 30 minutes.
Roll warm tarts in powdered sugar.

title: enchiladas
directions: *For
beef
enchiladas,
brown meat first.
For chicken enchiladas, boil chicken 30 to 45 minutes, then shred.

title: beefalo cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine with 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Fill pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Toss cheese with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 10 minutes more. Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Regular beef can be used.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon, crumble and drain. Save 1 tablespoon of bacon grease to add to clams. Chop and saute lightly the onions.
Add all ingredients back to pot (12-quart). Add approximately 1 quart water. Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes, stirring, then simmer for 2 hours.
Grate raw potatoes and add to pot, if you want it thicker or add additional water if too thick after 30 minutes. Add salt to taste.

title: jambalaya
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, cook garlic in butter for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Heat to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 25 minutes.
Add shrimp. Cook covered 5 to 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: southern pone cornbread
directions: Sift and measure meal.
Add salt and shortening.
Mix into dough with cold water and let stand a minute, adding more water if necessary.
Shape into small pones and place on hot, greased shallow pan, leaving space so they will not touch.
Put into hot oven for 10 minutes, then reduce to medium.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
If gas oven is used, place under blaze until slightly browned, then into oven about center with moderate heat.
Serve with vegetables.

title: wintery day bean soup(2 quarts)
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in a large kettle.
Cover with water.
Add salt and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts of water and ham. Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add onion, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper if desired.

title: frozen pumpkin dessert
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the gingersnap crumbs.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes, onion and beans. Place in large bowl.
Add cheese, corn chips and hamburger mixture.
Mix well, adding Catalina as desired.
Serve immediately.

title: relish
directions: Pour canning salt over the first 3 ingredients and let sit overnight.
In the morning, drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Add together and cook for 1/2 hour.
Makes 12 pints.
Use any kind of hot jar for packing.

title: baked steak with mushrooms and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat steak. Brown steak in butter over medium heat and remove.
Saute onion until soft. Add mushrooms and cook 1 minute.
Add beef stock and bring to a boil. Season with salt and pepper. Place meat in shallow baking pan in a single layer.
Pour liquid over and cover with aluminum foil. Bake 20 minutes, then add potatoes. Bake another 40 minutes or until done. Remove from pan; add half and half to liquid.
Heat, but do not boil. Serves 4.

title: roast beef and veggies
directions: Peel and slice veggies.
The night (or morning) before cooking, rub both sides of roast with meat tenderizer.
Let stand until 1 hour before preparing the roast.
Then marinate with Woodies barbecue sauce.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Brown slightly over char que coals.
When slightly brown, place in Dutch oven on top of veggies (salt and pepper to taste).
Use garlic on roast before cooking covered.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple well (using coconut, do not drain).
Layer in greased 13 x 9-inch pan all ingredients in order listed.
Use dry cake mix.
Place sliced margarine evenly over the other ingredients; do not stir.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Beat eggs and add pecans and vanilla.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45
minutes.

title: honey mustard chicken bites
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces. Dip chicken pieces into 3/4 cup dressing. Coat with stuffing. Place chicken on a baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Mix remaining dressing and orange juice in saucepan. Heat through. Serve with chicken for dipping. Makes 40 appetizers.

title: broiled whole lobster on grill
directions: Broil over medium hot coals, turning from time to time, about 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove stomach and fill with melted butter. Serve on heated plates with melted butter and lemon juice.

title: rice-stuffed peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Cook in boiling water for 10 minutes; drain.
Place in baking dish.
Mix ground beef, cooked rice, egg, salt, onion and enough tomato juice to moisten.
Fill peppers.
Pour remaining tomato juice over peppers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together; bake for 1 hour at 425°.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat together. Add rest of ingredients except corn bread.
Drop corn bread on top of casserole by spoonful. Bake at 350° until corn bread is done.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
In a large frying pan, heat butter.
Mix in green onion, pepper (if using onion, mix in now) and cook until tender over medium flame.
Add rice and meat. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: collards (2)
directions: Put turkey wings in large pressure cooker, along with some spices from the recipe and 3 to 4 cups of water.
Bring to a boil until spigot pops, 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
There should be 2 to 3 cups of liquid.
Wash collards thoroughly and cut away thick stems and chop coarsely.
Put chopped greens in pressure cooker in turkey liquid (leave in turkey) along with pearl onions, sugar, salt, both peppers and garlic powder.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes after steam starts rocking the spigot.
Remove from heat.
Taste and adjust seasoning.
Pour bacon pieces and drippings over top.
Stir in and serve.

title: veggie pizza
directions: First, separate sheets of crescent rolls into 4 rectangles; lay on a greased cookie sheet.
Press and seal seams.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and horseradish until smooth; spread mixture over entire baked crust.
Top with chopped raw vegetables (any substitutions will do).
Pieces should be small.
Top with grated cheese of your choice.

title: polish kraut and wieners
directions: Cut sausage into bite-size pieces.
Brown in large skillet. Add cabbage, onions and dressing.
Cook on low until cabbage is tender.
Serve with cornbread.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Melt 2 tablespoons oleo and add flour, salt, pepper, sugar, sour cream and grated onion.
Fold the green beans into the mixture.
Spread into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with Swiss cheese and finally top with buttered crushed corn flakes (or crackers).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked squash and apple casserole
directions: Pare, seed and cut squash into small slices.
Place squash and apple slices in 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.
Blend rest of ingredients, with a fork, fingers or pastry cutter, until crumbly. Distribute over squash and apples.
Prepare to here until ready to bake.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Pour into 2 raw pie shells.
Bake at 325° until set.
Beat egg whites; add 10 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on pies; return to oven only to brown meringue.

title: cheddar artichoke appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Slice French bread lengthwise and bake 10 minutes.
Let cool while preparing topping.

title: easy stew
directions: Brown beef and onion, drain and rinse.
Put in a large pot with other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to simmer and cook for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: moist layer cake
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 of the yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
(Other 2 yolks can be used in making fillings, if needed.) Add flour and milk alternately until all is used.
Add vanilla and soda water.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry chiffon pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and cherry juice.
Cook until of custard consistency.
Remove from fire and add cherries. Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to custard and let get very cold.
Beat whites of eggs until stiff, then add sugar and beat 1/2 minute.
Add this to custard.
Put in cold crust, heaping high.

title: spudin' spice cake with quick caramel frosting
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Add eggs and beat until thoroughly blended, then add soda combined with buttermilk alternately with flour, starting and ending with flour. Pour into greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lucky stars
directions: You will need a star cutter.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Do not cream butter and sugar, just dump everything in at once.
Beat all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a Pam sprayed Bundt pan.

title: apple crunch
directions: In first bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples as you slice into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In second bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Cut in margarine.
Add this topping and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and flour, one at a time, with flour between times.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients one or two minutes.
Pour into 2 large or 4 small loaf tins.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Top will crack.

title: almond bark candies
directions: Melt bark in large bowl in microwave.
Needs to be soupy, usually 6-8 minutes.
The bark will hold it's shape, so stir it to determine consistency.
Add peanuts and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
You can make any size that you want. This makes a lot of candy.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook beef, onion, garlic and oregano in oil for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make a well in the center. Combine the egg, milk and oil or shortening; pour into well.
Stir quickly just until moistened.
Add blueberries.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Combine, stirring well.
Spoon into lightly greased one-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: super bowl gumbo
directions: In an 8-quart pot, melt butter and saut bacon until cooked but not crisp. Add onions, shallots, celery and peppers, continuing to saut for 1 minute. Add tomatoes and garlic; saut 3 minutes. Add stock slowly, continuing to stir; add bay leaves and seasonings. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Add meat and seafood, according to taste and budget. Bring mixture back to boil; reduce heat to medium. Cover and cook for 10 minutes. Skim mixture and reduce heat to simmer, covering and cooking 15 more minutes. Add sauted okra; cover and cook for 15 minutes. Adjust seasoning to taste with salt, pepper, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.

title: microwave chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: In a dish combine rice, water and mustard.
In a colander toss together chicken and broccoli.
Place colander on a dish.
Cover and cook on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir once.
Stir chicken mixture, mayonnaise and milk into rice in dish.
Cover and cook on High 1/2 to 1 minute or until heated through.
Let stand covered for 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: carrot soup
directions: Heat oil.
Add vegetables, garlic and sugar.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add cloves, pepper and chicken broth; boil.
Reduce heat and cook 20 minutes. Remove cloves.
Process ingredients in blender until pureed. Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: potato salad with tomato salsa
directions: Cook potatoes about 25 minutes in boiling water; drain and rinse.
Halve potatoes lengthwise and cut each half crosswise; combine tomatoes, bell peppers, onion, chopped cilantro, jalapenos and olive oil in a bowl.
Season salsa to taste with salt and pepper.

title: cottage cheese "sour cream"
directions: Put ingredients in blender and process at High blend until creamy and smooth.
May want to add 1 tablespoon milk if seems too thick.

title: tri tip roast
directions: Take tri tip roast and marinate in Chuka's marinade for 6 to 12 hours prior to cooking.
Garnish in lemon pepper, roast seasoning and garlic salt.
Leave small bed of marinade on bottom of pan. Preheat oven to 325° until warm.
Cook roast for approximately 20 minutes per pound, checking periodically.
Baste roast with marinade occasionally.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Pour hot mixture over remaining ingredients and blend well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper or Reynolds Wrap.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: fish stew
directions: In frying pan or wok, fry bacon.
Add onions and peppers and cook until onions are transparent.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on medium until fish is done, approximately 15 minutes.
Can be served as is or over pasta.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo, water and cocoa.
Boil.
Pour mixture over flour, brown sugar and salt mixture.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake in cookie sheet (11 x 17-inch) at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge walnut pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, stir 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water and syrup. Heat over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add jello; let cool.
Put sliced strawberries into crust. Pour mixture over berries.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Stir all together except grated cheese in large saucepan until oleo is melted.

title: date balls
directions: Mix sugar, dates and margarine.
Cook slowly until dissolved (approximately 10 minutes).
Cool and add other ingredients; shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: delicious kraut salad
directions: Drain Bush's Best shredded kraut.
Put in mixing bowl. Combine sugar and vinegar in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes; cool slightly.
Pour over kraut.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry and coriander chutney(yield: 12 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan over medium heat. Cook until chutney is reduced to 3 1/4 cups, stirring frequently, about 1 hour 15 minutes. Cool. Discard cinnamon sticks. (Can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and refrigerate.) Good to serve with Pork Loin.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Add sauce, paste, puree, juice and water.
Chop onion and pepper and simmer this for 30 minutes.
Add ground beef and cook on low for 1 hour.
Add 2 cups spaghetti and simmer about 10 minutes.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: You will need one very clean brown bag.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, then add cream cheese, 7-up and remaining ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Place chocolate, sugar, and vanilla in blender.
Heat half and half and butter in microwave until scalded.
While hot, pour over blender ingredients.
Beat on high speed until smooth and thick. Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Children love to make their own sundaes!

title: tomato salsa
directions: Finely chop onion, garlic, cilantro and jalapeno peppers (for a sauce that is less hot, remove seeds from the peppers before chopping).
