Mix together and add the tomatoes, lime juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well until the tomatoes are partially liquified, but lumpy.
For a smoother salsa, put all ingredients in a blender and blend into a smooth consistency.
Keep salsa in refrigerator for 2/3 hour before serving.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all in a jar.
Refrigerate several hours before use.

title: angel food candy
directions: Slowly boil the first 2 ingredients until 290°.
Remove from the heat and add the baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour onto a large baking pan.
Let cool, cut, then dip in melted chocolate.
Allow to cool on wax paper, making sure all pieces are fully coated with chocolate.

title: *dough for pita
directions: Mix flour and salt in a large mixing bowl and make a well. Slowly add the water, working the mixture with your hands until the water is absorbed and a soft dough has formed.
Let dough rest for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli; place in a large bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain thoroughly.
Break bacon into small pieces; add to broccoli. Add sunflower seeds, raisins and onions; mix well.
Prepare sauce by combining the remaining ingredients.
Pour the sauce over the broccoli mixture; toss.
Refrigerate the salad at least 3 hours before serving.

title: bananas foster
directions: Peel bananas and cut in half lengthwise and then crosswise. In a skillet or chafing dish heat brown sugar and butter over medium heat until mixture melts.
Add bananas to the sugar mixture and cook, uncovered, for 3 to 4 minutes, turning once.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and drizzle liqueur on top.
In a small saucepan, beat rum until warm.
Ignite and pour rum over banana mixture. Serve over ice cream.

title: rice the fast way 2(servings:  6)
directions: In 4-quart pressure cooker, place approximately 1 1/2 cups water or until about 2-inches of water is in bottom of cooker. Place 2 1/2 to 3-cup stainless steel bowl into cooker on top of water.
In bowl, place rice, 1 1/2 cups water and salt.
Seal cooker and bring to steady rock for 5 minutes.
Wait for pressure to escape before unsealing.

title: cheese sauce(microwave)
directions: Melt margarine in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually blend in milk, stirring constantly.
Cook on Medium-high for 3 minutes or until thickened.
Stop and stir with wire whisk 3 to 4 times during cooking.
Add cheese; stir well. Cook on Medium-high about 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Wash and soak vegetables in 1/2 cup salt and 8 cups water. Soak 1 hour.
Wash and drain.
If too salty, rinse again.
Put everything together in very large boiler.
Let this come to a boil.
Pour up into pint or quart jars and seal.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour in a greased pan and bake for 30 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper with squash.
Cool and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish with buttered bread crumbs on top until set in center at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and beat until mixed well.
Bake at 350°.
Yields 3 layers.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Cut beef in half making 2 slices 1 1/2 inch thick.
Cook garlic, onion, green pepper in butter and saute until soft but not brown.
Blend in soup, drain mushrooms & add with olives, pimento, stuffing & pepper.
Place between meat slices.
Roast in 450 degrees for 15 minutes and then 350 degrees for 30 minutes for medium rare.
Add stir fry veggies or tossed salad for quick meal.

title: bonbons
directions: Melt together margarine and chocolate chips.
Add milk, flour and vanilla.
Mix well and wrap 1 teaspoon of dough around 1 Hershey's Kiss.
Bake at 350° for just 6 to 8 minutes.
They may not look done, but they are.
Drizzle with melted white chocolate. Makes about 45 to 50.

title: maple walnut apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Lightly spoon flour into a dry measuring cup; level with a knife. Combine flour, sugar, oats and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon in a medium bowl; cut in butter until crumbly. Stir in walnuts. Combine apple and remaining ingredients in a large bowl; toss well. Spoon apple mixture into an 8-inch square baking dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with crumb mixture. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm (with ice cream!). Contains 208 calories.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour in pie shell. Bake 20 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza quick
directions: Half French roll lengthwise.
Top with pizza sauce, meat substitute, pineapple and cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook meat together until crumbly and drain. Add onion, garlic, soup, tomatoes and peppers. Add Velveeta cheese and stir into mixture until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: red lobster caesar salad dressing
directions: Using a medium size wooden salad bowl, mash and spread the anchovies and the garlic with a fork and run the inside of the bowl with it.
Adding the vinegar and mustard, blend thoroughly.
Using the fork, add the olive oil and the coddled (meaning to cook in simmering water for 1 minute) egg yolk.
Mix together and add the worcestershire, lemon, pepper and parmesan cheese.
You add the croutons and the lettuce to the dressing not the other way around. Toss the salad until everything is coated with the dressing then serve in individual bowls.

title: cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cheese its
directions: Soften margarine at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients, adding Rice Krispies last.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together Jell-O and pineapple; over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Add sugar and cream cheese.
Continue to stir over low heat until cheese has melted; mixture will be lumpy.
Cool until slightly jellied.
Fold mixture into Cool Whip and 1 1/2 cups strawberries.
Decorate top with remaining strawberries and refrigerate until firm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding according to pkg. directions.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and cool whip.
Add pudding to cream cheese mixture.
Layer cookies and pudding mixture, making several layers. End with cookie crumbs on top.
Can be served in a new flower pot container and garnished with gummy worms as a novelty.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well in glass bowl or jar. Marinate chuck roast or other cuts of beef at room temperature for at least 4 hours.
Grill to taste.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash
and
onion until tender. Drain. Add other ingredients and beat. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: red cake
directions: Add
vinegar to soda.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and
fluffy.
Add
eggs,
one
at a time.
Sift together flour, cocoa,
baking powder and salt.
Mix milk with vanilla and	food coloring.
Add
to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir	in
soda
and vinegar.	Bake in 9-inch layer cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts.
Add bananas to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in cranberries.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Place livers, onion, garlic, bay leaves, thyme, water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil; cover and cook at bare simmer for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; let mixture sit about 5 minutes. Take out solids with slotted spoon and put into food processor. Process, adding butter piece by piece.
Add pepper and liquor and process 2 more minutes until mixture is completely smooth. Refrigerate until firm.
Garnish with capers.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and save 1/2 of juice.
Toss pineapple and bread together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased glass Pyrex dish. Cream eggs, butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 juice of pineapple; mix well again.
Pour mixture over pineapple and bread. Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered, in middle of oven.
Good with pork or ham.

title: v-8 biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and sugar in medium bowl; mix well. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add enough juice to form soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Yield: 18 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Put into salad bowl or a bowl that you would serve in.
Add Italian dressing, olives and shrimp or crab meat (or both).
Toss; refrigerate before serving.
Toss salad again in bowl just to saturate with dressing.
Enjoy.

title: spicy chicken wings
directions: Fry wings.
Mix honey, barbecue sauce, wing sauce and hot sauce.
Put chicken wings in mixture.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: sweet pecan smoked beef or pork ribs
directions: Boil ribs until tender but not falling apart, about an hour. Cut into serving sizes, about 3 servings per side of ribs. Dip in sauce and put in a covered roasting pan. Cook in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: john wayne's cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove seeds from chiles and dice.
In large bowl, combine cheese and chiles.
Pour in well buttered, shallow 2-quart casserole.
In large bowl, mix at high speed the egg whites to stiff peaks.
In smal bowl, mix egg yolks, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Fold egg whites into milk mixture. Drizzle over cheese and chiles.
Bake 30 minutes, then remove from oven.
Put sliced tomatoes in a ring around top of casserole. Return to oven and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter no-bake fudge
directions: Mix well (until creamy).
Roll into 1-inch balls or press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Tastes great refrigerated.

title: vanilla yogurt ice cream
directions: Whip whipping cream.
In a large bowl, combine yogurt, milk and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Cover.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.

title: sweet and sour lil smokies
directions: Place all ingredients in a slow cooker until sausages are tender.

title: hot pickled wieners
directions: Boil little smokies to get grease out and drain.
Boil vinegar, water and sugar and add smokies.
Add remaining ingredients and put in jar hot.
Then refrigerate.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Melt butter in large Dutch oven.
Saute green pepper and onion until peppers are crisp-tender.
Stir in chicken, mushrooms, pimiento, soup, milk, garlic powder and salt.
Drain spaghetti and add to mixture. Toss.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: lena's squash surprise
directions: Peel the squash, then slice.
Mix with all other ingredients and fry until tender.

title: macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar, flour and Karo. Mix in coconut.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until light brown.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat eggs, add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add cocoa, flour and salt.
Melt butter, Crisco.
Add to mixture and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add pecans if desired.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add flour mixture and all other ingredients.
Chill.
Roll in small balls the size of a walnut. Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl; mix well with a fork. Add shortening; mix with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat together with fork 1/2 cup water, the vinegar and egg.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough in 5 portions and, with hands, shape each portion in a flat round patty.
Wrap each in plastic or waxed paper and chill at least 1/2 hour.
Recipe makes two 9-inch double-crust pies and 1 pie shell or about 20 tart shells.
Dough can be left in refrigerator up to 3 days.
It can be frozen until ready to use.
Thaw until soft enough to roll.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat sugar, oil and egg.
Add milk and molasses.
Combine dry ingredients; add to liquid mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.

title: hurry-up meat loaf
directions: Remove ham from the can. Leave in one piece or slice in serving slices.
Spread ham with ketchup and heat thoroughly.

title: classic lasagna
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna.
In baking dish, spread 1 cup sauce, then alternate layers of lasagna, sauce, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: wild rice and asparagus salad
directions: In medium saucepan, bring chicken stock to bowl.
Add 1 cup rice; reduce heat and simmer covered for about 45 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Cut asparagus into 1-inch lengths and steam until tender crisp.
Place in a bowl of ice water to stop cooking process.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients with asparagus.
Add cooled rice.
Toss to mix well.
Refrigerate and chill covered for about 3 hours.
Serve on beds of lettuce.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, oil and sugar well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Bake in jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin-ricotta cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray an 8-inch spring-form pan with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle bottom of pan evenly with graham cracker crumbs. In a blender or food processor, puree remaining ingredients until smooth; pour mixture into prepared pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely on rack. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 8 servings (3 POINTS per serving).

title: gluten stew (mechado)
directions: Place all the ingredients in a pan.
Add water (2 cups), just covering the mixture.
Boil for 20 minutes, until the potatoes are cooked and sauce consistency is to your liking.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in melted shortening.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is just tender. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; add 1/2 cup broth to chicken along with the tomato juice.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.

title: water colors
directions: Mix vinegar and baking soda in bowl.
When mixture stops foaming, add cornstarch.
Mix well.
Divide mixture into small piles.
Add food coloring, different color to each pile.
Mix (optional:
add 1/4 teaspoon glycerine).

title: creates-its-own-crust coconut pie
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add milk and flour, blending well.
Add coconut.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chicken and put in casserole dish. Place chicken on top of mixture and bake for one hour at 350°.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix cream cheese well.
Whip cream stiff; mix in pecans, mayonnaise and preserves.
Drain pineapple; place on lettuce. Fill center with cheese mixture.
Place cherry on top.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Pour onions, tomato juice, tomato soup and tomato paste into cooked hamburger.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Add sugar, ketchup and mustard.
Simmer.

title: microwave mexican bean dip
directions: Place sausage in a large glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir several times.
Add beans, cheese, peppers, pimento, parsley and remaining seasonings.
Mix well.
Microwave on Medium-high for 8 minutes.
Stir after 4 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.
Dip may be frozen.
Makes 16 servings.

title: zucchini bake
directions: After baking, brush breads with melted butter to soften crust and to enhance color.
If you want a crisp crust, omit brushing with butter.

title: cheesy taco casserole
directions: Cook hamburger with the taco seasoning.
Melt the cheese in the hot macaroni.
Layer the cheese macaroni, hamburger, macaroni and hamburger in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomato and sliced green or black olives.

title: velveeta salsa dip(chili con queso)
directions: Microwave ingredients 5 minutes after cutting the Velveeta cheese into cubes.
Stop after 3 minutes and stir.
Can be heated in pan on your stove about 10 minutes, stirring often to blend cheese and picante sauce.
This can be kept warm while serving by using a chafing dish with candle.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: apple salad
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients until blended; add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill 30 minutes or until like unbeaten egg white. Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking dish. Cover and chill 3 hours or until firm.
Serve with whipped topping. Makes 6 servings.
Prep time:
35 minutes; chill 3 hours.

title: fried plantains
directions: Remove the skin of the plantains and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Heat the vegetable oil in frying pan.
Cook plantains over low heat. Grind the garlic cloves and mix with water.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Cut beef into 1/4-inch strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and brown meat in margarine.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Serve over hot rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit cup soup
directions: Chill this Scandinavian specialty for a few hours before mealtime to serve frosty cold.

title: quick lemon tart
directions: In a bowl, mix condensed milk and lemon juice. Fold in yogurt. Pile into shells.
Chill in freezer for 30 minutes.
Top each with a lemon slice, if desired.

title: fudge
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; cook until soft ball.
Remove and cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into mixer; add butter and vanilla.
Beat at speed 8 on mixer for 6 to 8 minutes, until candy loses glossy look.

title: edible modeling clay
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Can be shaped by imagination. Be sure hands are very clean first.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir occasionally as it is setting so that it is mixed well.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry cake mix and melted margarine together.
Pat 3/4 of this mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, building up the edges.
Spread the cherry pie filling over the cake mixture.
Mix the walnuts with the remaining cake mixture and sprinkle it over top of the cherries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Mix well in a 4-quart container or larger.
Store in freezer, mixing every day for 3 days.
Mix 1/2 glass of slush with sour soda.

title: angel food cake icing for diabetics
directions: Mix orange juice and yogurt together well.
Mix in Cool Whip (regular or light), and spread on cool cake.

title: apple pie
directions: Make pastry first.
If apples lack tartness, sprinkle with 1 tablespoon lemon juice, if desired.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to sliced apples and toss to coat fruit.
Fill a 9-inch pie plate and dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cover edge with foil.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°. Remove foil and bake 20 to 25 minutes more, until crust is golden. Cool and serve.
Bake at 375°.

title: apple raisin cake
directions: Mix well the oil, eggs and vanilla, then add flour, baking soda, salt, raisins, chocolate chips, nuts and apples.
Mix well. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Use a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Serve with Cool Whip or frosting.

title: caramels
directions: Mix all together in heavy pan or skillet.
Stir continuously. Test in cold water for chewiness desired.
Pour into 9-inch square buttered Pyrex.
Do not scrape pan; put scrapings in another pan, as it makes your caramels too hard in the center. Cut desired size.

title: popovers
directions: Beat together with rotary beater until smooth.
Pour into well-greased deep muffin cups 3/4 full or oven-glass cups 1/2 full.
Bake 425° until golden brown for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 5 to 9 popovers.

title: fit for a president cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Stir in chips.
Drop batter by well rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Makes 7 1/2 dozen.

title: oreo delight
directions: Soften ice cream and crumble cookies.
Mix together with electric mixer until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and instant coffee (optional).
Mix together, then spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Freeze.
Serve by cutting into squares.

title: couscous provencale
directions: In a heatproof bowl, pour boiling chicken stock and 1 tablespoon olive oil over couscous.
Cover; let stand for 5 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
In another bowl, combine remaining olive oil, diced zucchini, mint, parsley and lemon juice.
When couscous is cool, fold in zucchini mixture and chill for at least 30 minutes, then season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: grandma annie dykema's date bread
directions: Cut up dates into small pieces.
Add 2 tsp. baking soda. Bring water to a boil, pour over dates and baking soda; set aside. In bowl put beaten eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and melted butter.
Mix well; add cooled date mixture and nuts; mix well.

title: easy creamy broccoli soup
directions: Mix all and get soup hot enough to melt frozen broccoli and cheese.
Serve hot.

title: lela's spice tea
directions: Mix together and store in a fruit jar.
Place one or two teaspoonfuls into a cup of boiling water.
Add more sugar, if desired.

title: quick quesadilla
directions: Lay tortilla on a paper plate and spread with sour cream. Sprinkle cheese on top, then add tomatoes and chives or scallions. Add a spoonful or so of salsa to taste. Fold tortilla in half. This can be done ahead of time. Cover the plate with plastic wrap and refrigerate until you are ready to cook it in the microwave.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain well.
Combine other ingredients except crumbs.
Add to broccoli.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: squash bisque
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and carrot.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Cover pot and saute for 10 minutes, until tender. Add potatoes, squash and stock.
Simmer over low heat for 25 minutes or until tender.
Put mixture in blender and puree until smooth.
Return to pot.
Add cream and milk.
Cook until heated. Sprinkle with salt, white pepper and cayenne to taste.

title: butter rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° or until done.
Take out and shake pan to loosen from sides.
Leave in pan and pour syrup over cake.
Let set 30 minutes.

title: glazed spice bars
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and mix well.
(This can be mixed without a mixer.
Dough will be stiff.)
Pack into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread glaze over top while hot.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields about 48 squares.

title: german's sweet chocolate pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in large microwavable bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk until well blended.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped topping if desired.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until pie can be cut easily.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix and heat thoroughly.
Two ounces equals 1 meat.

title: ritz pineapple side dish
directions: Put pineapple in greased baking dish. Mix flour, sugar and cheese and sprinkle over pineapple. Cover with crackers and pour margarine over the top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serve warm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients and stuff into cavity of medium size turkey.
Roast turkey in medium oven at 325°.
It should be done when the popcorn blows the rear end off the turkey.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake.
Punch holes in cake with a straw.
Slowly pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut over it.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Slowly heat soup, milk and cheese until the cheese melts. Mix macaroni, minced onion, tuna and soup mixture together and put into a greased 1 1/2 to 1 3/4-quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dessert bars
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Measure and set aside 1/2 cup cookie dough; pat remainder into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spoon blueberry or strawberry filling over dough.
Break off small pieces of remaining dough and scatter over filling; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: mexican dinner with crazy crust
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce, tomato and cheese. Mix well.
Spoon into crazy crust.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomato and cheese. Serve with taco sauce.

title: spaghetti al pesto
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package. Drain.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients in electric blender. Blend at high speed until mixture looks almost like a paste but with some specks of parsley visible.
Toss with spaghetti until spaghetti is completely coated.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a buttered baking dish. Top with topping.

title: cauliflower with buttermilk sauce
directions: Trim cauliflower of leaves and stalk and break into flowerets. Steam cauliflower with water until crisp-tender.
Mix together buttermilk, mayonnaise and mustard; toss with steamed cauliflower. Put into ovenproof casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and place, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 3 servings as an entree or serves 4 as a side dish.

title: blender meat loaf
directions: Crumb crackers in blender.
Place hamburger in a large bowl (room temperature is easier to work with).
Pour crumbs over hamburger.
Place onions, eggs and tomato sauce in blender until smooth paste is formed.
Pour mixture over hamburger and crumbs. Mix with hands.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tandy kake
directions: Scald together milk and margarine and set aside.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients with milk mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well. Pour into well-greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread peanut butter over top while cake is hot.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: ruby salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water over medium heat until cranberries have popped and are cooked.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Let cool.
Stir in apples and chill until set.
Yields 12 servings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Drop with ice cream scoop.
Flatten slightly.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
(They make very large cookies.)

title: blue ribbon frozen snickers
directions: Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs and place in an 8 inch square dish. Mix all other ingredients together. Carefully spread into dish, so as not to disturb crumbs. Freeze until firm. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving. Cut into 8 equal servings. Garnish with a fresh sliced strawberry.

title: spam creole
directions: Heat in large frying pan
the
oil
and
rice,
stir in onion and green pepper.
Cook
and stir until lightly browned. Add hot water, tomato
sauce, salt, pepper, mustard.
Bring to boil. Cook, stirring until
thick.
Add strips of sliced Spam (or Treat, works as well.) Cook 3 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in pan and add 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Add 1 tablespoon dry mustard and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add carrots and stir until covered with glaze and heated.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Cut stem end from red pepper; remove seeds.
Slice center part into 8 thin rings for topping; chop remaining to make about 1/2 cup.
Saute pepper and onion in shortening, stirring often, for 5 minutes or until soft.
Combine beef, bread crumbs, spices, eggs and milk in large bowl; blend in sauteed mixture, then fold in cheese cubes.
Pack lightly into a 6-cup casserole; turn out into a greased shallow pan.
Score top in crisscross pattern with knife.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Saute saved red pepper rings in margarine, turning once, just until slightly wilted.
Arrange on top of loaf.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: braised chicken thighs with spicy tomato and ginger sauce
directions: In a medium frying pan, heat oil over moderate heat.
Brown thighs on both sides, skin side first.
Salt and pepper while browning second side.
Drain thighs on paper towels and set aside. Drain fat from frying pan except for 2 teaspoons.
Add tomatoes, garlic, ginger, chili and sugar and cook over moderately high heat for about 8 minutes.
Reduce to a low simmer.
Return thighs to skillet.
Cover and braise slowly for 20 minutes.

title: pepper oil
directions: Heat oil in a skillet to 300°.
Add peppercorns and fry 15 minutes.
Strain oil into a glass for storage.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Combine soups, broth and green chilies. Add chicken and heat thoroughly.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, celery, pepper, onion and peas.
Mix the mayonnaise and sugar.
Add this mixture to the top of the peas. Add a layer of cheese. Top with crumbled bacon.
Serving Size:
8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dice apples.
Sprinkle sugar over apples.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, egg and oil.
Stir by hand, then add nuts. After, mix well.
Pour into cake mold that has been greased with shortening (not oil) and floured.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef and sausage loaf
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender but not brown.
Combine eggs with next 4 ingredients and cooked vegetables.
Add beef and sausage and mix well.
Pat mixture into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and drain excess fat.
Let meat stand for several minutes before slicing.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan the crushed pretzels, sugar and melted butter mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Beat together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and egg.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip; pour over pretzel crust.
Mix together the jello, water and strawberries.
Let cool to a jelly like stage and pour over top of cream cheese mixture.
Let cool until solid.

title: waffles
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar; cool slightly.
Add egg yolks, sour cream and buttermilk.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Add to mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add 1 more cup of flour and 1 more cup of milk; this takes out the richness.
Soft when cold.

title: banana bread for diabetics
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg in mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Put oil, eggs, sugar and bananas in blender. Puree until smooth.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: cheerios mix
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Brush jelly roll pan with butter (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Heat sugar, syrup, butter and salt in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and nuts until well coated.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen mixture with metal spatula.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour.
Store in covered container.
Makes about 8 cups of snack.

title: spaghetti and sauce
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, sweet pepper, salt and pepper. Drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, pepperoni, sausage and cheese.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Pour sauce over to serve.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: wild rice casserole(serves 6)
directions: Drain water from rice.
Mix all ingredients in an ungreased casserole, saving a little of the cheese to garnish the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Good with steak, chicken and salad.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick butter together over low heat and set aside.
Cream together sugar and 1 stick of butter; beat well. Add eggs, soda, flour, salt, buttermilk and vanilla.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Bake in a Bundt pan.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift together the flour and 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Combine orange slices and dates and mix well.
Cream the butter until light, then gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Add eggs, one at a time, to the creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Combine soda with buttermilk and add alternately with flour mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add candy mixture and blend. Pour into tube pan (greased and floured) and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: stain remover for clothes
directions: In a full machine washer load of warm water, dissolve ingredients.
Soak clothes in washer overnight or until stain is gone.
Try smaller amount in a bucket for a longer period of time. The mixture can be kept and used over and over again.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Set aside potatoes.
Measure 1 cup reserved liquid, adding water if necessary; set aside.
Peel and finely chop onion.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook until sauteed.
Add flour; season with pepper.
Gradually add potatoes, reserved 1 cup liquid, milk and sugar.
Stir well.
Add cheese and ham.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Cut up the eggs coarsely.
Add celery, grated onion, seasonings and mayonnaise.
Mix lightly.
Serve in lettuce cups. Garnish with strips of pimento, chopped parsley and stuffed olives.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crescent italian casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix together with tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese. Separate rolls and top with 1 teaspoon sour cream that has the basil and oregano mixed.

title: clam chowder
directions: Add all vegetables to pan and add enough water to cover.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Melt butter and add flour, blending until smooth.
Add half and half and keep stirring until thick and smooth.
Add to the vegetables and add clams.
(Don't boil with the clams or they will become tough.)

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash and peel mushrooms.
Arrange them in a serving dish and pour lemon juice and olive oil on them.
Sprinkle the mushrooms with salt and pepper and marinate for at least 2 hours.
At serving time, drain them and spear with cocktail picks.

title: sauteed vegetables
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute peppers and onions until crisp and tender.
Add mushrooms and saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Season with salt.
Good served with steak or roast beef. Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter chocolate preacher's delight
directions: For Crust:
With a fork, cream margarine, flour, and nuts together until crumbly.
Spread crumbled mixture evenly in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake crust at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let crust cool completely before filling.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until brown.
Let cool; remove from pan.
(May also cook in 7 layers and frost with cream cheese frosting.)

title: nell's five bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and spices. Simmer 20 minutes.
Drain all beans except pork and beans; stir into meat mixture.
Place in oven until well heated.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg and applesauce. Sift flour, cinnamon, cocoa, cloves and salt.
Add raisins and nuts to this mixture.
Add to applesauce mixture with the hot water in which the soda has been dissolved.
Be sure some of the flour mixture is the last addition.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° in greased and floured pan.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and sprinkle into the bottom of a well Pam-sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sour cream and vanilla.	Sift dry ingredients together and add to eggs and cream; mix well.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Check with toothpick; 9 x 9 pan.

title: jailhouse cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts, brown sugar and whipped cream.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with nuts and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream when serving.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix ingredients well and roll into 1-inch balls and dip in powdered sugar.
Place in refrigerator to cure.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts and coconut.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top.
This can be placed in 2 (9-inch) pie shells made of vanilla wafers or used as pudding in dessert cups. I prefer a vanilla crust and place in large casserole.
Place your pie in oven long enough for the pecans and coconut to slightly brown.
Put in refrigerator.

title: cheese soup
directions: In large pot, combine celery, onions, bouillon and water. Bring to a boil for 15 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes and vegetables.
Simmer 40 to 50 minutes.
Just before serving, add 2 cans soup and cheese (cut cheese into cubes for faster melting). Heat until cheese melts and soup is heated through.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in melted butter.
Coat with crumb mixture.
Place in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: weight watchers sausage
directions: Combine ground beef (or turkey) and bread crumbs; mix well. Add salt, pepper, sage, cayenne pepper and water.
Mix well. Shape into roll.
Wrap into wax paper.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix eggs, flour, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add butter and cut spinach in chunks.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Serve with fruits, cookies or cake cubes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook onion and oleo.
Add milk and soups to oleo.
Add cheese and heat until it has melted.
Stir in chicken.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Alternate layers of chicken and chips, ending with chips on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbles appear.

title: angel food dream
directions: Combine Cool Whip and yogurt with wire whip.
Add strawberries.
Tear cake into small pieces; add to mixture. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serves 12 to 16.
(This is very low-fat!!!)

title: good dessert
directions: Put crushed crackers in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan (enough to cover to your desired depth).
Pour oleo over all.
Whip pudding, milk and ice cream.
Put on top of crackers.
Freeze.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with crackers that are crushed.

title: veal saltimbocca
directions: In frypan, brown garlic lightly in oil, then add spinach. Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Spread spinach on bottom of a lasagna dish. Pound veal cutlets to 1/4-inch thin.
In skillet, over medium heat, melt butter and brown veal on both sides.
Place veal over spinach.
Add sherry to pan and loose brown bits.
Pour over veal. Place Prosciutto over veal and bake in
preheated oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender; drain and cool. Mix together remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 days.
Drain and turn into serving dish.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature. Whip until fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk while continuing to beat until well blended. Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend all well. Pour into crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours before topping with cherry pie filling.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Place chocolate in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts. Set aside and let cool. Cream shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in melted chocolate. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to chocolate mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in vanilla and pecans. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely. Spread Fudge Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Bone when cool.
Crush Doritos. Dilute chicken soup with 1/2 can of broth from boiled chicken. Layer crushed Doritos, chicken, peppers and chicken soup.
On top of this, spread the can of Cheddar cheese soup.
Sprinkle with a few of the crushed Doritos.
Bake in a 325° oven until it is bubbly.
Serve with a salad and Doritos.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain well; sprinkle Chili-O mix over meat and onion and stir it around.
Sprinkle some chili powder onto meat.
Stir in beans and simmer about 10 minutes. Gradually stir in tomato juice.
Simmer 30 minutes or longer. Serve in individual bowls and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: crock-pot macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni for 5 minutes and drain.
Put in crock-pot margarine and grated cheese.
Beat eggs and evaporated milk; stir and pour over cheese.
Put drained macaroni in and stir all.
Add salt and lots of pepper.
Cook covered for 4 hours on low.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine beef, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Form into small balls.
Place in large glass baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
In saucepan, combine soup, water and ketchup.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover with glass lid or foil. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done.

title: mrs. snyder's crumb cake
directions: Work first three ingredients together.
Set aside 1/2 cup for topping before baking.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 375° preheated oven.
Makes 2 (8-inch) round cakes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft-ball stage. Add salt, vanilla and peanut butter and beat.

title: cranberry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Beat together the cream cheese and mayonnaise; gradually add lemon gelatin.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Whip cream; fold into lemon mixture.
Fold in marshmallows.
Spread over top cranberry layer.
Top with chopped nuts.
Chill until set.
Serves 12.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix and pour into square pan and congeal, then add topping.

title: grandma desmet bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter; put aside. Measure water into bowl.
Add yeast.
Stir.
Stir into milk mixture.
Add eggs.
Add 1/2 of the flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in the rest of the flour.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in large greased bowl.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and shape into 4 small loaves, 2 large loaves or 2 large braids.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for small loaves or 375° for 25 minutes for large loaves.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Drain can of pineapple and save juice.
Put pineapple in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese mixture over top; dot with margarine.
Pour juice over all. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: round steak
directions: Pound flour in steak and brown in skillet.
Mix bouillon cube, mushroom soup and water in skillet where meat has been browned. Heat together and pour over steak.
Bake, covered, for 2 to 3 hours at 350°.
May be served over rice.

title: kraut salad
directions: Toss together and refrigerate overnight.
Pimento would be okay to give the salad color, if no red pepper.

title: roasted garlic crab
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place cracked crab in roasting pan. Drizzle olive oil over crab.
Drizzle melted sweet butter over crab.
Add peeled garlic cloves, salt and pepper.
Squeeze half a lemon over crab.
Toss everything and roast for 15 minutes. Squeeze the other half lemon and add parsley.

title: bubble bath
directions: Light oven, get out bowl, spoons and ingredients.
Grease pan; crack nuts.
Remove 18 blocks and assorted ninja toys from table. Measure 2 cups flour.
Remove Lachlan's hands from flour.
Wash flour off of him.
Measure one more cup of flour to replace flour on floor.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in sifter.
Get dust pan and brush up pieces of bowl which Lachlan knocked on floor. Get another bowl.
Answer doorbell.
Return to kitchen.
Remove Lachlan's hands from bowl.
Wash Lachlan.
Get out egg.
Answer phone.
Return.
Take out greased pan.
Remove 1/4-inch salt from pan.
Look for Lachlan.
Get another pan and grease it.
Answer telephone.
Return to kitchen and find Lachlan.
Remove his hands from bowl.
Wash shortening off him.
Take up greased pan and find 1/4-inch layer of nutshells in it.
Head for Lachlan who flees, knocking bowl off table.
Wash kitchen floor.
Wash table.
Wash walls.
Wash dishes.
Wash Lachlan.
Call bakery and order cake. Lie down.

title: t.v. snacks
directions: Melt margarine in shallow pan with garlic salt, onion salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and nuts.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Stir every few minutes.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Use fresh marshmallows for best results.
Yield:
24 (2 x 2-inch) squares.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter. Mix in peanut butter and confectioners sugar to make dough. Form dough into balls and freeze. Later, melt 1/3 of chocolate in microwave on 50% power. Use toothpick to dip peanut butter ball into melted chocolate. Let set. Wrap in individual decorative foils.

title: chicken with mushrooms and tarragon
directions: You will also need wax paper cut to fit a casserole dish.

title: squash pudding
directions: Peel, cube, stew and drain squash.
Mash well and measure to make 2 cups.
Mix well, adding coconut last.
Bake in 400° oven in greased pan until brown and inserted knife in middle comes out clean (about 30 minutes).

title: chicken nachos
directions: Cook chicken breasts and remove skin.
Shred with a fork. Place in skillet.
Add onions, salsa and seasoning mix (prepared as directed).
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
On a cookie sheet or pizza pan, place chicken mixture and cheese. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Remove and add cubed tomato on top.
Use chips to dip.

title: super dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put all ingredients into crock pot and let cheese melt.

title: sweet-sour cabbage(for 2)
directions: Saute bacon bits.
Leave in skillet with grease.
Add cabbage and apple and lightly saute.
Add brown sugar.
Stir well.
Stir in salt, vinegar and water.
Cover and cook on low heat about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine pretzels, sugar and butter.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool. Blend cream cheese and whipped topping; spread over pretzel layer. Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of hot water.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Drain pineapple and stir it and strawberries into gelatin when thickened.
Pour over first 2 layers.
Chill several hours until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat eggs, water, shortening, bananas and about half of the cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix, oats, chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.
Remove.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Pour in large baking dish.
Cook ground beef and drain.
Mix soups, pepper and onion together.
Pour over beef and macaroni.
Mix well, cook for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cosette's veggie casserole
directions: Mix veggies, soup, sour cream and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Put onions on top. Bake an additional 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Use as much of each ingredient as you need.
Break spaghetti in 3 places and boil, then add other ingredients; season to taste.

title: microwave mystery chocolate cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients and 1 cup water; mix well. Pour into lightly greased glass tube pan.
Mix frosting as directed on package.
Spoon evenly over cake batter.
Do not allow frosting to touch side of pan.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes. Turn pan; microwave for 8 more minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Invert onto cake plate.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Add shortening and mix.
Add flour and soda; mix.
Drain fruit cocktail and stir in.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: similar to red lobster garlic biscuits
directions: Before baking, cream together butter or oleo, sour cream, garlic powder and parsley flakes.
Spread on biscuits and bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In 3-quart casserole layer sliced zucchini, then brown hamburg and chopped onion and put half of this over sliced zucchini. Layer 1 cup shredded cheese, then remaining hamburg, then 1 cup shredded cheese.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over all and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: anytime casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add Sloppy Joe mix, water, paste and corn.
Stir.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples, oranges, nuts and celery.
Stir all together and add sugar.
Set jello and gelatin as directed.
Add ground mixture to "soft set" jello.
Put into a container and return to refrigerator to set until firm.

title: lois murray's eggplant souffle
directions: Peel the eggplant; cut in small pieces and boil until tender. Melt butter; blend in dry flour and add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
When thick, add the other ingredients with the well-beaten yolks of the eggs.
Last, fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites, place in a greased baking dish and bake in a moderate oven about 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together for 2 minutes.
Pour into two loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crispy lemon fish
directions: Clean, wash and ry fish thoroughly with towel.
Dip in beaten eggs.
Salt and pepper fish and roll in commercial potato flakes.

title: butternut apple crisp
directions: Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon, salt, squash and pie filling.
Spoon into 10 x 6 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over squash mixture.
Bake uncovered about 45 minutes longer or until squash is tender. Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nut bread
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine egg, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until combined.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on a rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: diet chicken
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
except chicken, in plastic bag. Add chicken and shake to coat.
Put in shallow baking dish and bake, covered,
for
45 minutes at 350°.
Take out and drain. Bake, uncovered,
an
additional 20 to 30 minutes.
May add a little garlic
powder
or
flakes to dry mixture, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix and shake well.
Pour over slaw and vegetables.
Better if left overnight in refrigerator.

title: johnny appleseed filled cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Stir in cream and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt until blended.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut rounds.
Place apple butter on one round and place another round on top.
Press edges together. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: vanilla-caramel custard(flan)
directions: We first prepare the caramel.
Melt the sugar in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at medium heat.
Cover all the sides of the pan with the caramel.
Let it cool off while you continue with the recipe.

title: chicken and broccoli stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, stir-fry chicken in oil until brown.
Add broccoli, pepper and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry until tender.
Mix broth, soy sauce, garlic, ginger, cornstarch and sugar and add to skillet.
Bring to a boil one minute or to taste.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly, using a very large bowl or pot.
Store at room temperature in any container with a lid.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix margarine and bread crumbs.
Put half of mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Save other half for topping.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until well done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1
egg and 1 stick melted oleo; save 1 cup to put on top.
Mix well and press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cola chicken
directions: Saute till clear.
Put in chicken and brown both sides.

title: italian chicken
directions: Bake chicken breasts in broiler and cover with foil at 325° until tender.
Remove and set aside.
In large pot, saute bell pepper, onion, mushrooms, garlic, Italian herbs and oregano in 1/2 cup of wine and olive oil until tender.
Add the Prego sauce and other half of wine.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Place noodles and chicken breasts and cover with sauce in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While baking, melt caramels with milk and butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
When cake has baked 15 minutes, pour caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Cover with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts and bake for 20 minutes longer.
Cool and serve from pan.

title: shotgun nachos(a great superbowl snack!)
directions: Spread canned chili straight from the can onto chips.
Top with Velveeta cheese and your favorite toppings.
Heat on cookie sheet in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Spoon on picante sauce and serve warm.
Touchdown!

title: crispy oven baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Process corn flakes, cheese and spices in blender.
Dip potatoes in butter, then corn flake mixture. Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: favorite pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Measure 3/4 cup Spray (vegetable shortening).

title: turkey and stuffing pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pat stuffing evenly into a 9-inch pie pan. Press on the sides, too.
Sprinkle turkey and cheese in pan.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over turkey.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: brandy slush
directions: Put in freezer. Mix 2 scoops in 8-ounce glass.
Fill glass with 7-Up, Slice or 50/50.

title: onion chip dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with chips.

title: apple crumbles
directions: Mix sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and cinnamon.
Put apples in cake pan; coat with mixture of flour, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix together butter, brown sugar, oatmeal, 3/4 cup flour and baking powder until crumbly and spread over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° until apples are soft.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: 1st Layer:
Brown ground chuck and drain well.
Add taco seasoning and follow instructions on back of envelope.
Pour meat into oblong baking dish.

title: picante sauce
directions: Add all ingredients together.

title: secret ingredient chili
directions: Brown seasoned meat and onion; drain.
Add beans, tomatoes and chili mix.
Simmer 10 minutes; add mashed potatoes.
Simmer on top of stove or in oven for 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
Add water to make chili thick or thin as you want it.

title: talvina
directions: Cook meat, onion, salt, green pepper and Worcestershire sauce for 15 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients with meat mixture and layer in 3-quart baking dish with noodles and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6 or 8. Can do ahead.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine all except 1/2 cheese and 1/2 onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or 8 minutes in the microwave.
Place remainder of cheese and onion rings on top.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered, or 1 minute in microwave.

title: glazed strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup powdered sugar with strawberries. Set aside for 30 minutes. Cream together remaining powdered sugar and cream cheese; blend in vanilla and cool whip. Pour mixture into pie crust. Drain strawberries, saving juice. Add enough water to make 1/3 cup. Mix cornstarch, food colorings and juice. Cook until thick. Stir in berries. Spoon over filling. Chill. May be made in individual graham cracker shells.

title: potato primavera(excellent as a hearty main dish meal; low in calories and fat)
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Wash and prepare vegetables, cutting into bite sized pieces.
Wait to steam vegetables until potatoes are 10 minutes from being done.

title: icebox cake
directions: Crumble graham crackers and mix with melted butter; put half in bottom of pan.
Save half for top.
Melt marshmallows in top of a double boiler with milk.
Cool.
Combine marshmallows, whipped cream and fruit cocktail.
Pour in pan and top with remaining graham cracker topping.
Chill and serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine.
Mix corns, sour cream and corn muffin mix.
Place mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes, then sprinkle cheese on top and bake 30 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion with salt, pepper and oregano. Boil noodles in pot with salt and butter.
Drain when able to cut through noodles.
Stir in sour cream.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Place drained meat mixture on top of noodles.
Add 1/2 cheese.
Top cheese with tomato soup (straight from the can).
Fill soup can 1/2 full with water.
Make small holes with knife in top of casserole.
Pour in water.
Add remaining cheese.
Cook in 325° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients together and put on top of the apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: make ahead hamburger
directions: Mix well and form into patties at the size that suits you best.
Cook as you would any hamburger.
Freezes well.
Delicious and moist.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans. Mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in the chopped pecans.
Chill well.

title: butterscotch-marshmallow squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg well.
Add vanilla and beat thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in; add nuts. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with cut marshmallows.
Place them close together.
Return to oven for about 2 minutes, or until softened.
When cool, frost.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Blend all ingredients and spread on toasted English muffins or bread squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into pieces and set aside.
Melt butter and add dressing.
Mix well.
Mix broth and soups together over medium heat until heated through.
Pour 1/2 of dressing and butter mix into bottom of pan. Layer all of chicken over this.
Finish with the rest of dressing mixture.
Pour hot soup mixture over entire pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Place ground beef in bottom of casserole dish. Add layer of sliced onion and layer of sliced potato. Pour evaporated milk over top and add salt and pepper. Bake in 400 oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and add layer of cheese on top. Return to oven until melted.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup; bring just to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm (about 15 minutes).

title: pennsylvania dutch apple butter
directions: Quarter unpeeled apples.
Boil until soft.
Put through strainer.
Discard skins and seeds.
Combine apples with cider and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until thickened, stirring often. Add spices and continue simmering until of spreading consistency (2 to 3 hours).
Spoon into sterilized jars.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add garlic, basil, salt and parsley flakes; stir.
Add tomatoes and paste.
Set aside.

title: tomatoes florentine
directions: Cut a 1/2-inch slice from the top of each tomato. Carefully scoop out pulp (a mellon baller works well). Chop pulp. Drain and set aside. Place tomato shells upside-down on paper towels to drain.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, mayonnaise, soup, eggs and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole; sprinkle cheese over top.
In a frying pan, melt margarine and mix in stuffing.
Put stuffing mix on top of broccoli.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: champagne punch
directions: Blend crushed pineapple with its liquid, one can at a time, 15 to 20 seconds until thick in covered blender.
Combine blended pineapple and undiluted lemonade concentrate in a large punch bowl.
Stir in club soda and champagne.
Add ice and serve at once.

title: lemon pudding squares
directions: Mix flour, chopped nuts and butter together and pat in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Beat together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip and put on top of crust.
Beat puddings and cold milk together and put on top of cheese mixture, then cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix sugar, milk and chopped dates.
Cook to soft boil, stirring constantly.
Add butter and nuts.
Beat until stiff. Pour on damp cloth and wrap around, forming a roll.
This may be sliced when cold.

title: marinated mixed vegetable salad
directions: Barely cook the mixed vegetables in salted water.
Drain and cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together and marinate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix crumbs and butter; cook broccoli and drain.
Melt cheese and milk.
Stir in sauce. Put in casserole, put crumbs on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix.
Put in buttered baking dish. Top with 1/2 pound fresh crumbled bacon and 1/4 cup stuffed olives.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco mix
directions: Mix oregano, cornstarch, basil, pepper flakes and garlic powder.
Add chili powder and onion flakes.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1 1/2 tablespoons of spice mixture for each pound of meat.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Chill at least two hours.
Garnish with nuts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to directions.
Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can of onions and pimentos.
Bake 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ralph's barbecue sauce
directions: If cooking 4 chickens, double recipe.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°.
Serves 6.

title: jack's riverbend cafe barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add green onion and garlic.
Saute. Add shrimp, salt, pepper, Cajun seasoning and red pepper.
Squeeze lemon over shrimp.
Add barbecue sauce.
Saute 4 to 6 minutes. Don't overcook!

title: apple raisin cookies
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder. Cream shortening with sifted sugar.
Add vanilla and egg; beat well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with the combined evaporated milk and orange juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Put apples and raisins through food chopper and add grated orange rind and fold into mixture.
Drop from 1/2 teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: christmas cake
directions: Mix all but the last 2 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Add the last 2 ingredients.
Put in a greased and floured bundt pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: helen's chicken v-8
directions: Strip the skin from the chicken; remove the seeds from the green peppers and slice them into thin rings.
Place chicken in skillet.
Cover with pepper rings and pour in V-8 juice (or similar vegetable juice mixture) until chicken is submerged. Cover skillet; cook at 250° (low heat) until chicken is tender (about 2 1/2 to 3 hours).

title: bacon quiche
directions: Partially bake pie shell so that bottom will not be soggy in cooked quiche.
Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Beat eggs and milk; stir in bacon and cheese.
Mix and pour into partially baked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: veg dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: fajita in a pita
directions: Combine dressing and soy sauce over chicken breasts; marinate, covered, 6 to 8 hours, chilled.
Grill or stir-fry chicken slices. In skillet, saute all vegetables in marinade until tender-crisp. Fill pita halves with chicken strips and vegetables.
Serve with yogurt and picante sauce.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese over a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Heat to melt Cheddar.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use firm, fresh, medium size cucumbers.
Wash and cut into quarters or slices.
Put into container and pour boiling water over them; let set overnight.
Pack solid in jars.
Make pickling solution; boil 5 minutes.
Pour hot over cucumbers and seal. Yields 6 pints (more or less).

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease cookie sheet and have ready near microwave.
In 2-quart bowl, mix sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Mix well, carefully.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter; mix well.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto prepared sheet and spread with buttered spatula.
This step must be done quickly or mixture may harden in bowl.
Cool 30 to 60 minutes. Break into pieces.
Makes 1/2 pound peanut brittle.

title: fresh apple cake with caramel glaze
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt in a large bowl.
Beat well.
Mix soda and flour together; add to mixture.
Beat well.
Add apples and pecans.
Stir.
Mixture will be very thick.
Spoon into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Allow cake to cool completely before removing from pan (about 1 hour).

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl beat all ingredients with electric mixer (high speed) for 20 minutes.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells and chill. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip before serving.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix cream cheese with a little milk.
Gradually add rest of milk.
Mix in pudding.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Alternate layers of pudding with crackers.
End with crackers on top (3 layers of crackers, 2 of pudding total).
Cover with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Mix bread, ham and cheese in large bowl.
Layer 1/3 in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour and mustard; sprinkle one tablespoon over layer in pan and drizzle with melted butter. Repeat with each third.
Beat eggs with milk and pepper sauce until foamy.
Pour over layers in pan.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until puffed and golden.

title: italian chicken pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Cook broccoli, tomatoes, garlic, bell pepper and onion in broth in skillet over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes, stirring constantly until broccoli is crisp-tender and chicken is no longer pink in center.
Stir in spaghetti and remaining ingredients.
Toss until heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: aunt tollie's fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Mix eggs, buttermilk, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar well.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda together.
Add vanilla and apples.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix soup per the directions on the can, using half and half instead of water.
Add a pinch of tarragon while the soup is heating.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until thickened. Add Cheddar cheese; stir until melted.
Place potatoes in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 60 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: snowy night soup
directions: In a large kettle, saut onions in butter until tender.
Stir in beef and garlic and saut until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: meaty red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans in water.
Add onion during the last hour.
(You use leftover beans.)
The amount of beans depends on how many you are trying to feed.

title: ham steak with lemon for two
directions: Broil ham slices 5-inches from the heat for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, slice 1 lemon half.
Set aside.
Grate peel from other half and squeeze 1 tablespoon juice into a bowl.
Add peel, brown sugar and mustard to juice.
Turn ham over; brush with lemon mixture.
Top with lemon slices.
Broil 3 to 4 more or until ham is heated through.
Yields 2 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli per box directions until tender, but crisp. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer chicken on top.
Combine soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: * cake mix cookies *
directions: Add anything you like (nuts, raisins, chocolate bits, peanut butter or oatmeal).
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool 1 minute before removing.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook sweet potatoes until they are soft enough to mash.
Move to a large bowl and add ingredients.
After thorough mixing of ingredients, taste; if you need anymore of the ingredients, add in pinches.
Mix marshmallows into the mixture and put remaining marshmallows on top of potato casserole.
Bake in oven at 250° until marshmallows are brown and melted.
You can add pineapple or raisins if you like.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, water, syrup and peanuts in saucepan.
Cook to 300°, stirring constantly.
Take off stove and add soda; stir. Pour on aluminum foil and break when cool.

title: strawberry bread(first prize 1979 in dunedin, fl baking contest)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, then mix and make a well in center.
Mix in small bowl rest of ingredients.
Pour into well of dry ingredients.
Stir until all is moistened.
Pour into two well-greased standard loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: dough for cookie cutters(jason poti and family)
directions: Mix
ingredients
by rubbing between hands to mix until it forms
a
ball.
Add
raw egg if too dry and crumbly.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut cookies with cookie cutters.
Place on sprayed
cookie sheets.
Brush with raw egg white to decorate with
sugar,
etc.	Bake
10 to 12 minutes (less time if thinner cookies)
at
Let
stand 1 minute.
Remove and cool.
Keep dough not in use refrigerated and covered.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and put in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes until tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend oil, honey and lemon rind until nearly smooth; beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to oil mixture alternately with banana pulp, beating until smooth after each addition. Fold in nuts and raisins.
Place batter in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes, then remove from pan. Makes 1 large loaf.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix beaten cream cheese with sour cream, then mix in the other ingredients; let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt the margarine with the cocoa.
Beat the eggs and add the sugar and flour.
Add the vanilla and nuts.
Pour all ingredients in a
greased pie plate and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
The crust will form.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes and kielbasa(stove top method)
directions: Use amount of butter called for on package of potatoes and melt in skillet.
Add onions and saute until clear.
Add kielbasa. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, garlic powder to taste, cheese and milk (according to back of package).
Cook by the package directions.
Feeds 6 hungry people.

title: spinach almond sauce
directions: Place spinach, mushrooms and almonds in serving bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil; pour hot dressing over salad and toss.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Fold whipped topping into the cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry gelatin over that mixture and stir well to combine.
Fold in mandarin oranges.
Chill until firm.
Makes a large salad. Garnish with maraschino cherries for added color.

title: boneless pork chops with a slice of pineapple
directions: Thaw out boneless pork chops; put them in a shallow pan or a baking dish or whatever you desire.
You can boil them or bake them.
Preheat oven if baking, at 350°.
Bake pork chops for 1 hour or until done (or put under broiler).
When pork chops are done, put a slice of whole pineapple on top of pork chop.
Put meat tenderizer or your salt and pepper on them and return to oven or broiler until pineapple gets a little brown on top.
Take out of oven and enjoy.
If you desire, you can put the pineapple juice on top of the pineapple slices.
The juice will absorb in the pork chops when cooked.

title: tamale bites
directions: Combine cornbread crumbs, 1/2 cup of the enchilada sauce and salt.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Thoroughly drain meatballs; place in chafing dish.
Pour sauce over; top with shredded cheese.
Keep warm over low heat.
Serve with wooden picks.
Makes 60 to 80 appetizers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Mix rest of ingredients in a bowl.
Drip mixture over the butter in the pan, but don't mix!
Drain juice from fruit.
Spread over pan evenly.
Sprinkle some sugar over fruit.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until crunchy brown.

title: shrimp and clam fettucini
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute garlic in olive oil slowly. Add shrimp.
Strain clams (keeping the juice).
Add clams and mix, then add juice until warm.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Mix shrimp and clam mixture to cooked fettucini.
Mix with parsley and Locatelli cheese.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Grind fruit and boil about 1 hour.
Pack and seal.

title: pineapple breakfast rolls
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter in 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Add pineapple and cinnamon; mix well. Place biscuits on top. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until browned. Yield: 6 servings.

title: stuffing and pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Mix water and margarine in a bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, half of the peaches and syrup.
Arrange chops in baking pan.
Cover with stuffing mixture and top with remaining peaches.
Drizzle with mustard.
Bake 60 minutes.

title: ham and cheese squares
directions: Combine eggs, milk, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in ham, cheese and rice.
Bake at 350° in a 6 x 10-inch dish or 7 x 11-inch dish for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs in sour cream
directions: Soak
bread crumbs in milk.
Mix in ground beef, onion, egg and seasonings.
Shape mixture into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls. Melt butter
in	large skillet, add meatballs and brown on all sides. Cover; simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: ann landers' world famous meat loaf
