directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly, except bacon and tomato sauce. Put in loaf pan with 2 strips of bacon on top, if you want bacon flavor.
Pour the tomato sauce over the loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: mocha mousse
directions: Whip cream until it holds peaks.
Add 1/3 cup sugar, almonds and vanilla.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Melt sugar and syrup in pan. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together and pour over pressed mixture. Cool and cut.

title: incredible snow pudding
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water, then hot water.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Set aside until quite thick.
Then beat until light, fluffy and white.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat together.
Chill.
Serve with custard.
Great with Christmas dinner!!!!

title: georgia cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and bake in two greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: german sausage and beans
directions: Slice each knockwurst into 3 diagonal pieces; heat oil in a large skillet.
Saute knockwurst, pepper squares and onions until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add peas and tomato juice.
Stir to combine; simmer, covered, 10 minutes.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Blend together the cream cheese and sour cream.
Layer sour cream mixture, beans, taco sauce and other ingredients.

title: meringue for cream pie
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie while filling is still hot, sealing edges carefully to crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or golden brown.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Slice enough mushrooms to

measure 1 cup. Chop remaining mushrooms. Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat. Cook sliced and chopped mushrooms in butter about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are golden brown. Sprinkle with flour and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Gradually stir in whipping cream and broth. Heat until hot. Stir in sherry. Sprinkle with pepper.

title: apple pizza
directions: Form dough into a ball and roll into a 12-inch round pizza pan. Let rest 15 minutes.

title: challah bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/2 cup warm water; let stand 5 minutes. Combine oil and next 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium with an electric mixer until blended. Add yeast and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. (Dough should be sticky.) Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Turn out onto a well-floured board and knead 5 minutes. Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 1 to 1 1/2 hours (until doubled).

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak for one hour oatmeal and buttermilk or sour milk.
Mix together thoroughly, shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in alternately with oatmeal-buttermilk mixture.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix and spoon into egg whites.

title: frosted mint delight
directions: Have all ingredients chilled.
Melt the jelly and mix the crushed pineapple into it.
Dissolve the package of gelatin in 1 cup of the juice from the pineapple.
Mix the gelatin mixture into the jelly mixture.
Whip the cream.
Sweeten it with the sugar and fold it into the mixture.
Put into the freezer until firm.
Do not freeze solid.
Will serve 10 to 12.

title: mushroom croustades(appetizer)
directions: Carefully fit bread into lightly greased mini muffin tins, pressing gently into sides to form cups.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: hopping john
directions: Wash peas; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above peas.
Let soak 8 hours.
Drain.
Return peas to saucepan. Add salt pork, onions and green pepper.
Cover with water and simmer, covered, 2 hours or until peas are tender and water has cooked very low.
Add 2 1/2 cups of water, rice and seasonings to peas.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Add additional water if necessary.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all of the fruit including juice. Add the pudding and jello. Stir all together and refrigerate.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Let cream cheese and butter soften to room temperature.
Blend together with flour.
Chill one hour.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Press into ungreased tiny muffin tins.
Mix egg, brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, vanilla and salt.
Put half the pecans in each tin, add egg mixture and top with remaining pecans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool before removing from pans.
Makes 24 tassies.

title: dinner quiche
directions: Beat slightly the eggs.
Add milk and beat slightly.
Stir in shrimp, bacon, cheese, spinach, parsley flakes and salt.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until golden brown on top and center is puffed.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in rounds.
Spray 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Place a layer of potatoes in pan; add salt and pepper to taste and dribble bacon drippings over potatoes.
With a tea strainer, dust lightly with flour.
Repeat until all potatoes used. Pour milk over top layer; cover with foil and bake in 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.
Remove foil and brown lightly.

title: apricot bread pudding
directions: The night before, grease a large baking dish.
Put bread slices in baking dish. Drizzle butter over. Combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Squeeze water out of artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with a little Parmesan cheese on top before baking.

title: pork marengo
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onions in hot oil.
Transfer meat and onions to slow cooker and add remaining ingredients to skillet, scraping browned bits from bottom.
Pour over pork.
Cook on high heat for 4 to 6 hours.
Thicken gravy.
Serve over hot rice.

title: paradise salad
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix gelatin with 1 cup hot water; place in refrigerator until thick, but not congealed.
Drain juice from pineapple.
Follow directions on whipped topping mix package. Whip to desired consistency and add cream cheese and beat thoroughly.
Mix pineapple, nuts and cherries together.
Fold into cream mixture and then add gelatin, mixing all ingredients well. Pour into 8 or 9-inch dish and congeal.

title: spring chicken salad
directions: Cook oil and curry in small saucepan over medium heat for 4 minutes.
Add broth; simmer until reduced to 1/3 cup, 15 minutes. Whisk in sour cream, orange juice, honey, zest, lemon juice and salt if using.
Pour dressing into small, heatproof pitcher. Chill while preparing salad.
Arrange chicken, asparagus and orange sections on lettuce leaves.
Serve with dressing.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Fry onions and garlic in butter.
Add chili powder and tomatoes, simmer until mushy. Combine diced chicken, tomato mixture and spaghetti.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese, peas and diced olives.
Bake until bubbly.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put water on to boil for noodles.
In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Blend in flour. Add milk and stir constantly until thickened. When thick, gradually add shredded cheese. Remove from heat.
Drain cooked noodles.
Put in dish. Pour sauce over noodles and stir slightly. Top with rest of shredded cheese. Bake 20 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together refried beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on a 12-inch round serving platter.
Mix 1/2 cup taco sauce with sour cream.
Spread on top of bean mixture.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Pour remaining taco sauce over the top.
Serve with tortilla chips. Chill.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn bread.
Add corn bread.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cookies
directions: Cream shortening with the sugars, add eggs unbeaten, and sour milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry snowball cake
directions: Cut cake in half and tear one portion into small pieces. Spread pieces evenly in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese. Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add sugar and softened cream cheese to Dream Whip and mix well.
Spread mixture over the pieces of broken cake.
Tear the other half of the cake into pieces and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Mix berries with glaze and spread on top.
Refrigerate several hours before cutting.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: quick pineapple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add pineapple, flour, sugars and baking soda.
Mix ingredients well by hand.
Stir in walnuts and spread batter in an ungreased 13 inch x 9 inch pan.

Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 45 - 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. After cake cools, cover with cream cheese ginger frosting, then sprinkle additional walnuts on top.
To make frosting, beat together cream cheese, butter and vanilla in a small bowl.

title: aunt dovie's pound cake(50 years or older)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain well.

title: auntie gae's breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up 4 slices of bread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Brown, drain and crumble 1 pound of sausage, cut and crumble over bread.
Sprinkle 1 cup of sharp grated cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt and pepper to taste and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Prepare the night before and refrigerate if desired.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mash cream cheese with fork and add mayonnaise to make an easy consistency.
Add spices.
Remove peeling and seeds from cucumber and chop fine.
Add to cheese mixture.
Good for a spread on bread cut in rounds (served open-faced) or stuffed in cherry tomatoes. Sprinkle bread rounds or tomatoes with paprika.
Makes about 36 rounds of bread or 36 cherry tomatoes.
Scoop out pulp of cherry tomatoes and drain cherry tomatoes if used for stuffing.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Spread the almonds on bottom of pan.
Mix the cake mix, pudding, eggs, orange juice and oil and pour over the nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cherry dream cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Drop in shortening.
Add milk and extracts; beat 200 strokes.
Add egg whites and beat 250 strokes.
Add cherries and blend.
Pour into 2 lightly greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Cherry Fluff Frosting.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Bake the yellow cake according to directions on the box, using a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. As soon as you remove the cake from the oven, pour the entire can of pineapple (including juice) over the cake.
Let stand and cool to room temperature.
Mix the cream cheese, instant pudding and milk together with a mixer.
Spread over the cake.
Refrigerate until it sets up. Spread Cool Whip over the pudding mix. Sprinkle thoroughly with coconut. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Must be stored in the refrigerator between servings.

title: cavitini
directions: Brown
hamburger
and
drain.
Add pepper, onion, mushrooms and
Ragu
sauce.
Simmer
until peppers and onions are tender. Add
2 or 3 slices of American cheese.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain
and
add to the hamburger mixture.
Mix and pour into a casserole dish.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: neal's indian fry bread
directions: Pat the dough into 2-inch cakes.
Drop into hot oil, 350°. Fry until golden brown.
Serve with butter and honey.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine all fruit and stir in pudding mix.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Brown ground beef and saute onion.
Add pizza sauce, Cheddar soup, mushrooms and 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese. Simmer until cheese is melted.
Pour over cooked noodles in pan. Mix and spread evenly in pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Spread other 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese over top last 10 minutes.
Also can be done in crock-pot on low.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and roll into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: "no fail" pie meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water in little saucepan and bring to boil and let boil until clear (1 minute or so).
Beat egg whites until real stiff.
Fold hot mixture into stiff egg whites.
Put on pie, sealing edges to crust and bake at 400° until golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruited oat scones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; stir in fruit.
Add combined egg and milk, mixing until moistened.
Shape dough to form ball.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead gently 6 times.
On lightly greased cookie sheet, pat out dough to form 8-inch circle.
With sharp knife, score round into 12 wedges; sprinkle with combined cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Break apart and serve warm.

title: sprite pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until smooth.
Add one egg at a time and beat.
Add flour and stir.
Combine Sprite and lemon flavoring; mix into batter until smooth.
Bake at 325° in loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut top off peppers and remove seeds.
Mix meat, onion, egg, rice, crackers, salt and pepper.
Stuff generously into each pepper.
Place into heavy saucepan with tight fitting lid.
Pour tomato sauce and 1 can of water over peppers.
Bring to boil. Cover with lid and reduce heat to low; simmer for approximately 1 hour.

title: traditional jamaican christmas pudding
directions: Stone and stew prunes with sugar to taste, then chop fine. Stone dates and chop fine. Cut other fruits very fine, except currants.
Place all fruits in a large jar (omitting nuts).
Pour wine and rum on fruits and steep for at least one month.

title: tar heel hush puppies
directions: Stir, adding water to thick consistency.
Drop in deep fat (preferably Duke's peanut oil).
Cook at temperature of 375°. Serves 6 persons.

title: peach yum yums
directions: You will need aluminum foil.

title: egg salad
directions: Mash eggs.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
For a dip, use more mayonnaise to make thinner. This is real good on wheat thin crackers!

title: mom's oatmeal cake
directions: Mix water and oatmeal together and set aside. Mix rest of the ingredients together; then add oatmeal mixture. Stir until smooth. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes and let cool.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Do not overcook.
Drain and place in greased 2-quart dish.
Mix together the mayonnaise, cheese, celery and onion.
Spread this mixture over top of your vegetables in casserole.
Mix melted oleo and crushed saltines well.
Spread this crumb mixture over top of casserole. Place in a 350° oven and cook until golden brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Add all ingredients to dissolved gelatine. Mix well. Chill in the refrigerator.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Cook potatoes in butter until evenly coated.
Add water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 14 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Combine milk, soup mix and parsley. Stir in cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Add ham.
Cook until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.
Stir gently.
Ready in 30 minutes or less.

title: easy eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into small cubes.
Simmer eggplant cubes in saucepan with 1/2 cup water for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, crumble 2 slices of bread over eggplant.
Stir in Ricotta cheese, onion, green pepper, pimento, seasoning and unbeaten egg.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with shredded Lamagna Mozzarella cheese.
Crumble remaining slice of bread over top; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple griddle cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Beat eggs, oil, milk and yogurt.
Add to dry ingredients (fold to mix).
Gently add apples. Spoon batter onto hot, lightly greased griddle; turn when brown.

title: sugar-free blueberry crumble
directions: Combine blueberries with sweetener in bottom of small casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly and top the blueberry mixture with this. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Combine oil and flour in a large Dutch oven.
Cook over low/medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes, until roux is the color of a copper penny.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill for 24 hours before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: graham cracker crumb coffee cake
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; mix with crumbs.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugars. Beat in eggs (one at a time) and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating just to blend.
Stir in walnuts; spread in greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef with onions.
Drain.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread in bottom of a greased pie plate. Top with cheese.
In a blender, blend milk, eggs and biscuit mix. Pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: japanese shrimp bake
directions: Place shrimp in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with wine.
Combine crumbs, butter, parsley, garlic salt and paprika; sprinkle over shrimp.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Garnish with sprigs of parsley before serving.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Drain water from frozen broccoli.
Meanwhile, mix eggs, cottage cheese and melted oleo.
Add salt and corn meal mix.
Mix in drained broccoli and chopped onion.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix together the margarine, sour cream and flour.
Divide into 4 parts and chill until firm.
Roll each part out separately. Spread with preserves, coconut and pecans.
Roll up into a roll and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Slice while still hot, but not as soon as you take them out of the oven.
Approximately 15 minutes cooling time needed.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add egg and pumpkin; mix. Add milk.
Pour in unbaked pastry shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 pies.

title: mierbe teig(crust with peaches)
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Work as for pie crust. Handle as little as possible.
Chill about 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Roll 1/2 crust in an oblong shape.
Fill with drained peaches, brown sugar and small amounts of cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Cover with remaining crust and press edges together.
Bake at 500° for 1/2 hour.
Cool.
Make icing of remaining egg white (unbeaten), 3/4 cup sugar, butter and vanilla; beat thoroughly.

title: marvell's graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt butter, sugar and pecans together.
Put graham crackers into a cookie sheet and then spoon the mix over graham crackers. Let cook 8 minutes at 325°.

title: oven barbecued meat balls
directions: In a bowl, moisten bread crumbs with milk and combine them with meat, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into 24 meat balls and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: five layer cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cut venison into bite-size pieces.
Coat thoroughly with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown coated venison in butter with minced garlic and onions, over medium heat.
Add sliced mushrooms. (Two small cans of sliced mushrooms may be substituted.)
Drain excess butter.
Add lemon juice, Burgundy, consomme and a dash of salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Cover and cook slowly on extremely low heat for 15 minutes.
Ladle over cooked noodles or swamp.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry crunch pie
directions: Mix ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: coq au vin(chicken in wine sauce)
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, nutmeg and salt.
Brown in oil and butter.
Transfer to casserole.
Saute celery and onion until golden; stir in ham and seasonings.
Add to chicken.
Place quartered onion around chicken (stick onion with cloves if desired), add mushrooms.
Heat brandy, pour over chicken, ignite. Add wine, cover and cook in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze half of this recipe. When ready to serve, pour unfrozen punch over frozen punch.
This will be slushy.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a pan and stir over heat until everything is melted.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Stir in one package of yeast.
Gradually work flour into liquid, stirring and kneading as necessary, then let rise until double in bulk.
Knead well, put in covered bowl and refrigerate.
Make rolls and let rise 2 to 2 1/2 hours at room temperature.
Bake at 450° until light brown, about 10 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Clean romaine, then refrigerate.
Crush garlic clove; combine with oil in jar with tight cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Heat 2 tablespoons garlic and oil mixture.
Add salt, mustard, pepper, Worcestershire and anchovies.
Shake well; refrigerate.
Boil egg 1 minute.
Rub inside of wooden bowl with garlic.
Discard garlic; cut romaine.
Shake dressing well.
Pour lemon juice over egg. Crumble Bleu cheese; add grated cheese over all.
Add croutons and toss well.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package crescent rolls. Pinch seams together; smooth out. Beat together cream cheese (room temperature), sugar and vanilla. Spread over layer of dough. Top with remaining package of crescent rolls. Pinch seams together. Smooth out. Top with sprinkles of cinnamon sugar. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. When cool, cut into 1 x 2-inch bars. Serve cool.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse and drain lentils.
Place in pan with water.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add rice.
Meanwhile while cooking lentils, saute onions in olive oil till golden.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and egg. Mix soda with persimmon pulp. Stir into sugar and margarine mixture. Add flour (with spices mixed in), then stir in walnuts. Drop on greased cookie sheets. Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix eggs, powdered sugar, brown sugar, cocktail, soda, vanilla and flour. Beat; pour into pan. Top with pecans, coconut and brown sugar. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: rigatoni
directions: *Use as much juice as needed without making too runny.

title: gypsy chowder
directions: Combine ingredients in 3-quart kettle and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 2 hours, until lentils are tender.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries and apples through blender or food processor. (Use some pineapple juice, if using blender.)
Add pineapple and spices. Taste for sweetness. Add more sugar, if needed. Refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, just enough to thaw thoroughly.
Drain off water.
Mix together broccoli, rice, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Dump and spread in cake pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy caramel sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Mix well. Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches 220°, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in butter, whipping cream and vanilla. Serve sauce warm over ice cream or pound cake. Yields 3 cups.

title: south carolina low country dressing
directions: Mix meal, milk, egg and shortening.
Pour into skillet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
In large mixing bowl, put bread pieces and pour part of heated broth; let this soak, then crumble corn bread into bowl and pour remaining broth.
Saute onion in 1 stick of butter, then add this to dressing.
Add seasonings; mix well.
Should be very soupy.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 1 hour until browned on top.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add Marshmallow Creme and lemon juice. Mix well. Add food coloring, one drop at a time, until desired color is obtained.

title: tomato pie
directions: Slice tomatoes in bottom of pie shell.
Add onions on top of tomatoes.
Add bacon on top of onions.
Sprinkle a little cheese on top of bacon.
Continue another layer as before.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese together; add mixture for pie topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: garlic bundt bread
directions: Saute garlic in melted butter for two minutes.
Add parsley. Roll thawed bread dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls into melted butter, garlic and parsley mixture.
Place dipped balls in a nongreased Bundt pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and invert onto plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until set like custard.
Do not cover while baking.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Let cream cheese stand for 30 minutes to soften.
Mix taco seasoning mix, sour cream, cream cheese and Picante sauce in a bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Empty refried beans in a pan and heat until warm.
Adding a little water helps in spreading.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and lemon juice together.
Add to milk and beat all together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 2 hours. Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend cheese and margarine until creamy. Combine other ingredients with cheese mixture. Roll in palms about 2-inches long. Place on greased cookie sheet. Use fork to press. Bake in oven at 350° for about 18 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Bake in a covered roaster at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Mixture will be thick.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with meringue.

title: cheese and fruit crepes
directions: In a medium bowl, beat together eggs and milk.
Beat in flour. Let stand 15 minutes.
Melt margarine in large skillet (crepe skillet).
Make them thin.
Cook until golden brown.
In a blender or food processor, combine cottage cheese, 1/3 cup sugar and milk. Process until smooth.
Serve on crepes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Dip chops into beaten egg; pepper.
Press chops into bread crumbs.
Lay flat in a casserole dish.
Mix soups together and pour over chops.
Sprinkle cheese on chops.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: brazil nut snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter and sugar.
Beat egg and vanilla to light and fluffy.
Sift flour and salt.
Add to butter; mix with nuts and beat thoroughly.
Shape into 2/3-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes or until done. Cool cookies slightly, then roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 9 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: homemade chili
directions: Slowly cook hamburger and onions.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover; cook over medium heat for approximately 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and butter until fine crumbs are formed. Reserve 1 cup of this for topping. To the remaining crumb mixture, stir in remaining ingredients, except pecans. Spread in 2 greased and floured 8-inch round pans. Sprinkle with reserved topping mixture and pecans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. These freeze well.

title: deviled ham and mushroom stuffed tomatoes
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine over low heat for 5 minutes, let cool. Mix remaining ingredients (except tomatoes) in a medium side bowl.
Stir in mushrooms.
Chill.
Cut top fourth off each tomato and scoop out insides.
Fill with ham mixture, keep chilled until serving.
Garnish with snips of parsley, if desired.
Makes approximately 20 appetizers.

title: pineapple treats
directions: In frypan, pour juice from pineapple.
Cut sausage and put 1 chunk of pineapple on it.
Hold with toothpick.
Put into pan and heat.
Can also be done in microwave.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring the water and oleo to a boil and melt oleo. Add the flour. Stir until mixture leaves side of pan and forms a soft ball. Cool slightly. Add the eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased), over bottom and sides. Bake 35 minutes at 400°. Cool. This crust will raise up different places; don't disturb it.
Mix together the cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Spread on cake.
Spread the Cool Whip over the pudding.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except the boiling water.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer.
Sir in boiling water.
Batter will be very thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans, or 3 8-inch pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Place dry ingredients in bowl. Add liquids.
Mix well and place in buttered loaf pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp-avocado salad
directions: Peel, pit and dice avocados.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add shrimp and remaining ingredients.
Stir together and let stand while chilling, for several hours.
Serves 4.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage (scramble) and drain.
In a medium bowl, put sausage and tomatoes.
Cut cheese into chunks and put in a microwave for 3 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Stir.

title: aunt jean's enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and 1/2 of onion, drain well.
Put back in skillet on low heat, add seasoning and mix well.
Set aside for 15 minutes to cool.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Chop finely cabbage, pepper and onion.
Combine and bring to a boil sugar, cider vinegar, mustard seed, salt and turmeric.
Pour the hot mixture over the cabbage, pepper and onion.
Mix well and place in refrigerator.
Flavor improves after a day or two.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring
sugar,
milk
and butter to boil and boil 5 minutes. Cool.
Add	enough	powdered sugar until good spreading consistency.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until barely tender. Drain well.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients to soup mixture.
Sprinkle with bread cubes.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Mix one 3 ounce flavor of jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in 1/4 of a 1/2 gallon ice cream.
Pour into a glass 4 to 6-quart bowl.
Let set for about 1/2 hour in fridge.
Continue process until you have 4 layers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix eggs, broth and 1/2 can soup.
Add stuffing and chicken and mix.
Put in baking dish.
Mix 1/2 can soup and milk together and pour over stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage bits
directions: Mix all ingredients together (a food processor can be used). Roll into balls about the size of a quarter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot. May be frozen for later use.

title: mocha chocolate frosting
directions: Add about 1/2 teaspoon instant coffee dissolved in about 3 tablespoons hot water.
Mix until all ingredients are blended together.

title: tacos
directions: Fry meat; pour	off grease.
Add enchilada sauce, beans and seasonings.
Fry
tortillas;
fill with meat mixture.
Add cheese, tomatoes, lettuce and taco sauce.
Serves 8.

title: mint brownies
directions: Bake brownies as directed and let cool.
Mix the confectioners sugar, 1/2 cup butter and crme de menthe.
Spread on brownies and cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Season and flour chicken pieces; place in skillet and brown in hot oil until golden. Cover with water and boil gently until tender. Saute onion and garlic in bacon drippings; add to chicken with remaining ingredients, except corn meal and corn. Mix thoroughly. Add a small amount of water to corn meal, stirring until smooth. Add to chicken mixture and boil until thickened. Pour into a baking dish; top with creamed corn and bake in a 350° oven until brown. Makes 10 servings.

title: meaty baked beans
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain excess grease.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan.

title: cheese snack rounds
directions: Mix cheese spread and baking mix.
Shape into roll about 1 inch in diameter on lightly floured cloth covered board.
Roll in sesame seed, pressing lightly if necessary.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Cut roll into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 42 appetizers.

title: good casserole dish (salmon)
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix egg and milk and pour over noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger, onion and seasonings.
Drain.
Put this mixture over noodles.
Pour spaghetti sauce over this.
Put cheese and then pepperoni.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook covered (foil) at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Fold all ingredients together (except a little of cherries and whipped cream).
Pour into glass serving bowl.
Chill.
Garnish with remaining cherries and whipped topping.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: The Tbsp. baking powder is not a mistake.
That is what make the batter rise to the top.
Pour melted margarine into a 9 by 12-inch baking pan.
Mix white sugar, flour, milk, and baking powder.
Pour over the margarine.
DO NOT MIX!
Place the prepared fruit over the batter.
DO NOT MIX!
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon, then sprinkle over the peaches.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.
(This recipe could be used with apples and blueberries.) Frozen fruit may be used but should be thawed and drained.

title: baked fish
directions: Combine butter and lemon juice.
Dip each fish fillet in butter mixture and arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle fillets with salt, pepper and parsley.
Arrange lemon slices over fillets.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: garlic chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Drain and add tomato sauce, beans and chili mix.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and roll into small balls. Brown meatballs.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk together for 9 minutes.
Time, after it starts boiling, stirring constantly.
Add hot mix to the chocolate chips, butter, Marshmallow Creme and salt.
Beat until smooth. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased pans and let set overnight.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: chicken rotini tetrazzini
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in large saucepan over medium heat, melt butter; add onion.
Cook 3 minutes or until tender.
Dissolve chicken bouillon cube in hot water; add to onion mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling, stirring until sauce is smooth. Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Toss hot pasta and sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Combine with beaten eggs.
Add corn syrup, vanilla and nuts.

title: mallow cups
directions: You will also need mini paper cups (for candy).

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll dough into rectangle.
Spread eggs, oil and Parmesan cheese on bread dough.
Top with sliced pepperoni and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Place in greased bread pans and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Marinate ribs for 8 hours.
Cook, uncovered, 1 hour at 350° or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Pour Italian dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onion, chopped egg whites and add sieved yolks.
Mix with mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard. Fold into salad.
Add salt and celery seed to taste.
Chill 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Spread 1/4 cup pecans in a 7-cup ring (spray with Pam).
Press cheese mix into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: herb rolls
directions: Blend margarine, parsley flakes, dill weed and onion in a 9-inch pie pan; melt.
Cut biscuits in quarters and swish each one in melted mixture.
Arrange pieces, touching, in pie pan and bake in a 425° oven for 10 or 12 minutes or until brown.
Let stand a short time.
(Delicious for luncheons or buffet dinners.)

title: potato salad
directions: Add to potato mixture; it may not take all of it, just enough to moisten.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin into bite size pieces and brown in frying pan.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Saute onions and mushrooms.
Add to browned sirloin.
Add 8 ounces sour cream and stir over low heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add all other ingredients, saving 1/2 of nuts for garnish.
Shape into one large or two small balls.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: bayou blend
directions: Saute vegetables with 2 tablespoons of butter; add shrimp.
Mix 1/2 cup of butter with cream cheese, then add to vegetables, then add mushrooms and all soups.
Next add rice and stir.
Add crab meat.
Put in oblong dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: seven layer green salad
directions: In large pan start layers of vegetables with layer of lettuce, then continue with other vegetables.
Spread salad dressing on evenly.
Then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Do not toss at serving time.
Use large spoon to serve.
Serves from 8 to 12.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes; rub skins with oil.
Bake 1 hour at 400°. Allow potatoes to cool to touch.
Cut in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
(Pulp may be used for mashed potatoes!)
Cut shells in half crosswise and deep fry in hot oil for 2 minutes.
Drain skins on paper towel.
Place skins on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt, cheese and bacon.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 1 dozen appetizers.

title: baked squash
directions: Split each acorn in half; remove seeds and fibers.
Place in an ungreased baking dish, cut side up.
Into each well, add 1 tablespoon of maple syrup and 1 tablespoon of cream.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: lo-cal jello salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; chill.
One hour before serving, add
Cool Whip (more or less according to taste).

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients and chill in refrigerator. Garnish with red
grapes
rolled in egg whites and then in granulated sugar.

title: new potatoes baked with bay leaves and lemon
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly oil large, shallow baking dish. Add potatoes to dish.
Mix lemon juice, oregano, lemon peel, salt and pepper in bowl.
Whisk in oil.
Pour over potatoes; toss well. Tuck bay leaves around potatoes.
Bake until potatoes are golden brown and knife pierces centers easily, turning potatoes every 10 minutes, about 45 minutes.
(Note:
Depending on the age and water content of the potatoes, this can vary greatly, a little as 30 minutes to as long as 1 1/2 hours.)

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Brown pork chops; cover with sliced potatoes.
Pour on soup mixture.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.

title: key largo coleslaw
directions: Add lime juice to the chopped vegetables and mix thoroughly. Then add salt, sugar and mayo.
Again, mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: pecan bubble ring
directions: Thaw bread in refrigerator overnight.
Quarter lengthwise; cut each quarter into 8 cubes (32).
Combine dry pudding mix, brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Dip each dough cube into melted butter, then roll in pudding mixture.
Place in greased 6-cup ring mold in 3 layers.
Drizzle with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining pudding mix.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook onion and beef until onion is transparent and meat loses red color.
Add remaining ingredients except Chinese noodles. Cook until bubbly.
Put in casserole dish and cook until tender at 350°.
Sprinkle noodles on top and brown.

title: mom's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; chop and set aside.
Clean, wash and cut remaining peppers in half lengthwise; set aside.
Rinse spinach thoroughly; cook, drain and chop.
Chop onion; saute in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Add chopped peppers; cook until soft. Add chopped spinach; cook until oil is completely absorbed and dry.
In a bowl, add crushed crackers and cheese.
Moisten slightly with milk.
Add spinach mixture; mix thoroughly and add egg.
Mix well.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Cook on slightly oiled cookie sheet on each side for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat and cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together; drain.
Melt cheese in crock-pot on low temperature and add meat and all other ingredients.
Blend well.
Heat and serve with your choice of chips.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight.
Remove from refrigerator for 30 minutes before serving.
Serve on crackers.

title: beth's cheese spread
directions: Mix together all ingredients; spread on crackers.

title: parmesan chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut tip from each wing and discard. Cut wings into two pieces.
Mix cheese, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper together; place on a dry tray or baking sheet.
Dip each piece of chicken into melted butter, then roll in cheese mixture, coating well. Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 45 minutes, turning when brown.
Makes 8 servings as appetizers or snacks.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; spread with butter on both sides. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage until crumbly; drain well.
Spoon sausage over bread; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard; mix well and pour over cheese. Cover pan; chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, or until set.

title: spaghetti supreme
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in oil.
Add ground beef.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes, olives and salt; cook about 30 minutes more.
Add Worcestershire sauce, diced mushrooms, tomato soup and 1/2 of cheese.
Mix well with cooked spaghetti.
Put in a baking pan; sprinkle with remaining cheese and set in refrigerator at least 2 days before serving.
Bake 1 hour at 350° before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add bananas, salt and soda.
Mix in flour; stir until damp.
Add nuts; pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Cook for 30 minutes at 375°.
Freezes well.

title: dieter's pizza
directions: In skillet, cook meat and garlic until brown; drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, onion, oregano, fennel and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Boil gently, uncovered, about 30 minutes.

title: easy sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In a large bowl, beat together butter, sugar and eggs with an electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy, 3 to 4 minutes.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt; beat until well mixed.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Turn batter into well-greased 12 cup bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes, or until golden and a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes, then unmold onto a serving plate and cool completely.

title: dinner in a snap
directions: Place rice in a greased loaf pan.
Top with chicken and mushrooms.
Mix water, soup and sherry.
Top with cheese.
Cover snugly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken and rice are done.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add flour.
Cook, stirring, until bubbly.
Add next 5 ingredients; stir until thick.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Do not overcook.
Pour over toast triangles.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Add bacon.
Serve immediately.

title: butter flavor chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonful of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Do not overbake.
Cool before removing to wax paper.

title: apple cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and milk and beat well. Stir in dry ingredients and mix.
Add apples.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, spread with glaze.

title: not just any kraut
directions: Heat skillet and add 1 tablespoon butter, kraut and pepper, cut into thin strips.
Cut smoked sausage into chunks and add to other ingredients.
Fry until light brown or until peppers are tender.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cheese, butter and 10x sugar. Mix in oil and color.
Roll into balls; compress into molds. Dry 2 hours on wax paper. Freeze or refrigerate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: *One entire can of pumpkin will make 2 loaves if the rest of the ingredients are doubled.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: Combine cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg, blending well. Stir in applesauce.
Mix well (it will be stiff).
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Let dry in sunny window 4 days.
Store in plastic bags. Before drying, place ribbon or copper wire hanger on back.

title: tasty chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, cut in chunks and place in an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Add soups to mayonnaise, chicken broth and celery.
Mix and pour over chicken.
Pour stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: microwave barbecue chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place in microwave dish with meatiest side down and bigger pieces to the outside of your dish.
Pour whole jar of barbecue sauce over the chicken.
Cover with microwave Saran Wrap and cook on High for 25 minutes, turning halfway through cooking time.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook onions and mushrooms in butter until light brown; add soup.
Remove from flame and add whipping cream and pepper.
Stir until smooth.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage.
In iron skillet, melt about 1 tablespoon of margarine (may need to add more).
Add all ingredients and fry for about 5 minutes or less.
Cabbage should be wilted, but still a little crisp.

title: five bean salad
directions: Boil vinegar, water and sugar.
Cool.
Pour over drained beans and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add onion and pepper, slivered.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Clean seeds by rubbing off any fibers. Do not wash.
Measure seeds.
Combine every cup of seeds with one tablespoon of vegetable oil, olive oil or melted butter.
Spread seeds on baking sheet, or on bottom of a baking dish.
Sprinkle with one teaspoon salt or 1 teaspoon each of salt and curry powder.
Roast 30 to 40 minutes (stir frequently), until seeds are crisp and browned.
Cool and eat.
Store seeds in airtight container.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat together all ingredients except blueberries.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into lined muffin pans.
Bake in 400° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: ranch style pear preserves
directions: In large porcelain pot, pour sugar over fruit and let stand overnight.
Next day, simmer until fruit is translucent and juice becomes medium syrup, but still covers fruit.
While still simmering, pour into hot sterilized canning jars and seal with new, sterilized canning lids.
Let stand until cool without disturbing.
Lids will pop and be concave.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Stir sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Cook 5 minutes, without stirring.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir, mixing well. Put in oven at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes to coat corn.

title: mayonnaise dressing
directions: Process the eggs, mustard, salt and lemon until lemon yellow. Slowly add the oil.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cream, ice cream or lemon sauce.

title: cranberry souffle salad
directions: Mix gelatin, sugar and salt in small saucepan.
Add water. Place over low heat, stirring constantly until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat and stir in mayonnaise, lemon juice and rind. Blend with a rotary beater.
Pour into a refrigerator tray.
Quick chill in freezer 10 to 15 minutes or until firm about 1-inch from edge but soft in center.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 4-cup mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving plate.
Garnish with salad greens and mayonnaise.

title: better than sex chocolate cake
directions: Remove a spoonful of cake mix and use to coat the chips and nuts.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, eggs, oil, water, vanilla, pudding mix and sour cream.
Mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Turn into a greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool and frost.

title: spicy baked squash
directions: Slice squash in small pieces in pot with water.
Add onion and salt and boil until tender and most liquid has cooked away.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually blend in the flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop mixture by a tablespoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove from oven and press the M&M's on top of the cookies while they are still hot.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan simmer broccoli with chicken broth, chopped onion, thyme and nutmeg until tender, about 6 minutes.
Carefully pour into food processor or blender container and blend until smooth.
In clean large saucepan melt butter; stir in flour and cook 1 minute. Stir in milk and cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Stir in broccoli mixture.
Heat thoroughly.

title: oven barbecued beef
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Pour oil into skillet and brown each piece on both sides.
Transfer steaks to roasting pan.
Add onion and brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients to make a barbecue sauce and simmer in skillet 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over steaks in pan.
Cover.
Bake 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Chicken or pork chops may be substituted, proceeding in the same manner as for steak.

title: spinach pie breakfast
directions: Cook spinach and drain thoroughly.
Combine spinach, cheeses, eggs and seasonings.
Pour mixture into a square 9 x 9-inch pan (nonstick).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until golden on top.
Let cool, then cut into squares, wrap and freeze.
Reheat in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed potatoes
directions: Pierce skins of potatoes in several places with fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Brown sausage in large, heavy skillet, breaking up meat with a fork.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until onion is transparent.
Drain; stir in tomatoes and seasonings.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Keep warm.
Cut top quarter off potatoes; scoop out most of potato, leaving shell intact.
Add scooped potato portion to sausage mixture; toss lightly.
Fill potatoes with mixture.
Put under broiler until brown and hot.
Top with sour cream.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook celery in small amount of boiling salted water until crisp, about 8 minutes.
Drain.
Mix celery, water chestnuts, soup and pimiento in a 1-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with almonds in melted butter.
Sprinkle over ingredients in casserole. Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 cup flour, sugar and undissolved yeast. Add water and margarine to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 3/4 cup flour; beat at high speed 2 minutes. Stir in enough flour to make stiff dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes. Set in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Divide in 2 balls.
Roll and stretch to fit pans.
Place on greased baking sheets, sprinkled with cornmeal.
Shape edges of crust into a standing rim of dough.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread with sauce. Sprinkle with browned and drained sausage.
Top with cheese.
Bake about 10 minutes more.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine everything in a bowl and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is slightly browned.
Sprinkle with a little fresh lemon juice if desired.
Use shallow Corning Ware dish.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Butter the bottom of dish and add the fruit and water.
If using apples, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Work sugar, margarine and flour until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of fruit.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crackers, margarine and almonds.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers and margarine.
Place on top.
Sprinkle almonds on top of crackers. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ice cream topping for sundaes
directions: Cook over low flame stirring constantly until thickened. Serve warm over ice cream for hot fudge or butterscotch sundaes.

title: italian sausage roll
directions: Cook sausage and drain off grease, but keep the grease.
Use Pam on cookie sheet; preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out dough, but not too thin.
Sprinkle Parmesan on dough and then sprinkle 1/2 Mozzarella.
Put on cooked sausage and then rest of Mozzarella. Roll up the dough and make sure there are no open gaps anywhere (especially on sides).
When you put on the cookie sheet, make sure the top of the roll is on bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes, then brush grease on top of loaf and bake 15 minutes more.

title: pumpkin loaves
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and pumpkin.
Add spices to flour, then add to previous mixture.
Mix well.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°. Makes 2 small loaves.

title: sugar cookies no. 2
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out on floured surface and cut with seasonal cookie cutters.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased baking sheet at 400°.
Ice when cooled, if desired.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: You will need a large black skillet.

title: peanut butter cheesecake pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat until creamy.
Fold in peanut butter, milk and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Fold in 2/3 of Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with finely chopped peanuts.
Chill well before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Add yogurt, beat again.
Gently stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with your favorite fresh fruit.

title: banditos
directions: Simmer above ingredients for 40 minutes.
Add 2 cups cooked rice (if desired).
Serve over tortilla chips.
Add a layer of each of the following:
lettuce, tomatoes, grated cheese, onions, avocado, black olives and green pepper.
Top it off with sour cream and picante sauce. Each person can pile their own dish according to what they like.
(Chop onion, avocado, olives, tomatoes and green pepper small; the flavor is better that way.)

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken broth.
In blender, combine milk, cheese and flour until smooth. Add mixture to hot broccoli mixture, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in half and half. Serve.

title: lemon loaf
directions: After grating lemons, juice lemons and save separately. Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs and blend well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into the egg mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in the lemon rind.
Beat well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 45 minutes. (Note:
Can be blended in food processor if desired.)

title: date nut bread
directions: Cover dates, sugar and butter with boiling water.
Add all other ingredients, but soda, blending well.
Add soda, mix well. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cake test with toothpick.
Cool and invert onto a rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Simmer on medium heat until tender the first 6 items for about 20 minutes.
Add next 3 items, stirring constantly until thick. Stir in 4 1/2 ounces processed cheese (Cheez Whiz or Velveeta light).
Stir until melted.

title: make ahead meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; do not overmix! Shape mixture into 24 meatballs. Place formed balls onto a cookie sheet sprayed with no stick cooking spray. Place cookie sheet with meatballs into freezer. Once meatballs are frozen, transfer them into a plastic freezer bag. Store in freezer until ready to use. Meatballs may be defrosted and baked or baked frozen. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes if frozen, 15 to 17 minutes thawed. Always cook to an internal temperature of 160°.

title: scottish eggs
directions: Boil eggs until hard-boiled.
Peel eggs.
Wrap a small amount of uncooked sausage around each hard-boiled egg.
(Make sure none of the white from the egg is showing.) Place wrapped eggs in shallow pan and bake in oven for 30 minutes on 350°.
Remove from oven and enjoy.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir to mix well.
Cover; chill. Makes 2 cups.
Serves 8.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Make sauce with butter, flour, seasonings and milk.
Cook sauce over low heat, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add ham, cheese and noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into oiled 2-quart casserole and bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until top is light brown.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done (approximately 45 minutes).
Cut chicken into chunks.
Butter casserole dish and put chicken on the bottom.
For second layer, crumble 1/2 bag of chips.
For third layer, mix cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel together.
Pour over other layer.
For fourth layer, crush remainder of chips.
Top with Cheddar cheese soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cook sausage and drain well.
Mash fine.
Add eggs, cheese and spices.
Spread out each package of rolls to make large rectangle. Press together all seams well.
Put 1/3 of mixture on each rectangle.
Roll up lengthwise.
Seal ends.
Put seam side down on pan.
Brush with egg.
Bake about 30 minutes or until light brown at 350°.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: quick cocoa cake
directions: Bring to boil the butter, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar which has been mixed.
Stir until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in cake pan at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in cake.
Pour icing over hot cake.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix ingredients and add peaches.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan at 350° until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Layer twice in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave until bubbly and heated thoroughly.

title: orange supreme cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
When finished, punch holes in cake with a fork.
Prepare orange jello and pour over cake.
Place in refrigerator to cool, about 1/2 hour.
Mix together pudding, milk and flavorings.
This will make the frosting for your cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheese log
directions: Cream Philadelphia cheese.
Add all ingredients.
Shape into logs; refrigerate; roll in pecan pieces.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Partially thaw
hash browns and mix with other ingredients except parmesan
cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle
Parmesan
cheese
over
top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix together sugar, egg, vanilla, salt, soda and cocoa; mix well.
Add flour, oil and milk; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Makes about 18.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil. Add eggs and dry ingredients with buttermilk. Add vanilla, nuts, prunes and raisins. Pour into Pyrex pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugar, salt and oleo until boiling; cook 10 minutes more!
Add all ingredients; beat until thick.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: chili verde
directions: Lightly brown the pork.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper and saute.
Pour mixture into a crock-pot.
Add chilies, tomatoes, salt, oregano and cumin.
Add cilantro if you have it.
Add water. Cook 4 to 5 hours on high, longer if you want.
Thicken to taste with flour (if you like).
Serve on large tortillas topped with cheese (burritos).

title: topping for meat loaf
directions: This is enough for 2 loaves.
Mix together and spread on top before baking.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring water, butter and cocoa to a boil.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat together.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine, mix sugar & flour together.
Put in margarine and mix well.
Beat in bowl.
Put in buttermilk and beat with fork a few strokes.
Bake at 350° 34 minutes.

title: macaroni beef skillet dinner
directions: Cook the macaroni in boiling water according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Saute meat, onion and garlic in oil until the meat loses its pink color and onions are tender. Add pepper, tomato sauce, drained mushrooms, Worcestershire and Italian seasoning.
Bring to a boil and simmer gently for about 5 minutes.
Mix in the macaroni and simmer about 5 minutes more. Makes 8 servings at about 270 calories each.

title: emily's fruit compote
directions: Combine fruit and water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole. Cover; microwave at High for 5 1/2 to 8 1/2 minutes, until fruit is almost tender.
Stir after 4 minutes.
Stir in sugar.
Re-cover fruit; let stand 2 minutes.
Compotes may be served warm or cold. Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: steak and tomato gravy
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat on both sides.
Brown in large skillet on both sides.
Add remaining flour to drippings. Add onion, tomato puree and sugar, plus 1 cup water.
Cover and put in 350° oven and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
Add soup and milk. Simmer for about 15 minutes.
While simmering, cook noodles according to directions on package.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until soft; drain.
Chop up tomato and cucumber into small pieces.
Dice green onion and bell pepper.
Add vegetables to cooked spaghetti.
Pour salad dressing and seasoning over spaghetti-vegetable mixture.
Toss and refrigerate. Additional salad seasoning can be sprinkled to taste before serving.

title: city restaurant poppy seed cake
directions: Butter and flour 1 (10-inch) tube pan.
Set aside.
Combine poppy seed, honey and water in saucepan and cook over low heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until water evaporates, stirring frequently. Cool.
Cream together butter, sugar, lemon peel and vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add and combine thoroughly at a low speed sour cream, poppy seed mixture, salt and lemon juice.
Add flour mixture to poppy seed mixture. Beat at low speed until thoroughly combined.
Pour dough in prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for about 60 to 75 minutes or until cake draws from both sides of pan and center is dry when tested. Cover with foil if cake browns too quickly.
Cool about 15 minutes in pan.
Invert and cool to lukewarm.
Pour hot Lemon Glaze over cooled cake.
Makes 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Put on wax paper and let cool.

title: hearty chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles, in slow cooking pot. Cover and cook at setting 3 (low) for 6 to 8 hours or setting 5 (high) for 3 to 4 hours until chicken and vegetables are tender. Remove chicken pieces from cooking pot and set aside to cool slightly.
Increase heat to setting 5 (high) and add noodles, stirring to blend.
Cover and continue cooking for 30 minutes.

title: "frosted" carrot bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add remaining 5 ingredients until well blended.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar.
Beat well.
Add milk and mix, then add corn.
Top with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: butter barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter. Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer 5 minutes. If stored in refrigerator, warm before using.

title: lemon pie
directions: In iron skillet, mix the sugar, flour and salt.
Add the cold water, mixing well to make a paste.
Add the egg yolks; mix well. Add juice of lemons; mix well.
Cut up the butter or margarine. Add 1 cup boiling water, stirring well.
Add another cup of boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Remove from fire; let set 5 minutes.
Beat well.
Let cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: french onion rice
directions: Saute rice in butter in skillet or saucepan until lightly browned.
Add soup mix and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork and sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and cut out stems on mushrooms.
Boil caps in water for 5 minutes.
Dice stems and fry in butter; add onion, sherry, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Fry until brown and crispy.
Add Italian bread crumbs until mixture is solid.
Spoon into caps.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in warm coffee or water.
Mix all ingredients by hand.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: queso dip
directions: Melt all ingredients together over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: space pie
directions: Melt butter; mix flour, sugar, butter and finely crushed walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 15 minutes until golden brown in 2 pie pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Cool.

title: secrets in a biscuit
directions: Roll out biscuits, just enough to measure 5 inches across. Sprinkle some sugar and cinnamon on top.
Add a kiss.
Fold four corners in, almost completely sealing biscuit.
Gently roll the biscuit/kiss in sugar and cinnamon. Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Be careful, the kiss melts and is hot.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine and fill unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken or fish marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients, soak desired meats in marinade at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.

title: june merrill's fireside coffee
directions: Mix well; store in a tight container.
Use 3 tablespoons to a mug of boiling water.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Whip together the eggs; add the whipping cream, cheese and onion.
Place the bacon or sausage into the pie crust; add the filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread creamed cheese over bottom of flat dish.
Layer remaining ingredients, except chips, over creamed cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips at room temperature.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Mix all ingredients together and put in well buttered casserole dish.
Cook in a 325° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown on top.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add 1 egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add second egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla. Pour into baked pastry shell. Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with cherries and nuts. Chill in refrigerator.

title: fruited rice mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in airtight container.
To prepare, combine 1 cup mix with 2 cups water and 2 tablespoons butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until water is absorbed. Yield:
About 5 cups dry mix.
Each cup makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil and eggs.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with toothpick and pour cream of coconut over cake while warm.
Let cool and spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle frozen coconut on top and chill four hours.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and apples. (Batter will be stiff.)
Pour into greased and floured (13 x 9-inch) pan.
Add butterscotch pieces and pat down.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook the cut carrots in boiling water with salt until tender (don't overcook).
Drain and cool carrots.
Combine with onions and pepper.
Mix together soup, oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire, salt and pepper until blended well.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
This will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, cool. Stir in cottage cheese, cucumber and mayonnaise and chill until syrupy. Stir again and pour into a lightly oiled 1 -1/2 quart ring mold. Chill until firm. When ready to serve dip mold into lukewarm water for a few seconds, tap to loosen. Invert onto a serving platter. Place a bowl of Ruby Dressing in the center of the mold. Chill until ready to serve. If desired, garnish with halved cucumber slices or spiced apple rings. Fill center with leaf lettuce and serve dressing on the side.

title: cookie salad
directions: Prepare pudding with 1 cup milk according to directions on box. Add pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip. Crush cookies with rolling pin and add to the rest of the mixture.
Save a few crumbs to sprinkle on top.

title: chilled zucchini soup
directions: Place zucchini, onion, thyme, parsley and bay leaf in a medium saucepan with 1 cup chicken stock.
Bring to boil.
Simmer until squash is tender (about 10 minutes).
Remove bay leaf and parsley and puree mixture in a blender until of a uniform consistency. Strain the puree by pressing through a strainer with the back of a spoon.
Add remaining chicken stock and the rest of the ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve this soup with cold chicken and a light salad.
Makes 1 quart (4 servings).

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add just enough milk to make it thick enough to drop by spoonfuls into berries.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all in large bowl. When mixed thoroughly, pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Place in refrigerator overnight. Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: western pork chop dinner
directions: Brown chops in oil in large skillet; season with salt and pepper.
Mix all veggies with seasonings lightly; place in greased (Pam) 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over potato mixture.
Top with pork chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours or until chops and vegetables are tender. Serves 6.

title: easy sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in
a bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Pat dough out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Mix sugars with butter.
Add the egg.
Mix in flour until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan and cook at 350° until golden brown.
Let them completely cool before cutting into squares.

title: mile-high biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients
in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg and milk at once; mix until dough
forms
a ball.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and
knead	10
to 12 times.
Roll out 3/4-inch thick and cut
with
a
1/2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased sheet and freeze.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix ham, margarine, mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire in a bowl.
Split the entire package of rolls, all together, as one big roll.
Spread the ham mixture on both sides of rolls.
Sprinkle cheese (if grated) or place slices on 1 side of roll.
Place halves together.
Cut in squares and wrap in foil. Heat in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes about 50 to 60 rolls or squares.
Use as hors d'oeuvres.

title: caramel candy
directions: Brown 1 cup sugar.
Pour water over melted sugar and cook until it thickens. Add milk and other sugar to syrup. Cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Pour into mixing bowl and add flavoring. Beat until creamy. Add nuts and drop.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, chocolate and sugar; add butter.
Mix and press in pan.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill while cooking dinner.
Will be ready for dessert.
Can use other fruits, also.

title: homemade chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, sugars and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt (dough will be stiff).
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown 8 to 10 minutes (centers will be soft).
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies; 90 calories per cookie.

title: three golden apples coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and set aside.
Place apples in bowl, break egg over apples.
Add butter, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Stir dry mixture into apple mixture until moist.
Put into a 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs until blended.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Fold in all other ingredients.

title: barbecue bread
directions: Simmer until thick; place in refrigerator to cool.
Spread thickly on bread; sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and wrap loaf of bread in aluminum foil and heat in warm oven.

title: pumpkin pie cake dessert
directions: Bottom:
Mix together cake mix (reserving 1 cup of the mix) with melted butter, 2 eggs and spread this in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all together and simmer 25 minutes.
Place hot mixture in jars and seal.

title: catherine collier's pork chops and rice
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper, then flour.
Brown in hot shortening on both sides.
Put rice in greased baking dish. Put chops on top of rice.
On each chop, put a slice of tomato and a slice of pepper.
Pour consomme soup over it all.
Bake for one hour at 325°, covered.

title: strawberry-apple danish star
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to package directions, stirring in 1/2 cup confectioners sugar. After mixing, cover bowl of dough tightly with plastic wrap.
Let stand in warm place 10 minutes.

title: six week muffins
directions: Combine Raisin Bran, flour, sugar, salt and baking soda in large mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, mix together eggs, buttermilk and oil; add to flour mixture.
Mix well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and grated cheese; add sausage, blend well. Shape into small balls.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Store in plastic bag in the freezer.
Place frozen balls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Dry flounder fillets with paper towel.
Divide crabmeat between fillets.
Spread fillets with crabmeat.
Roll fillets. Secure with wooden toothpicks.
Place in buttered baking dish. Mix soup, pepper and mustard; spoon over fish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, and roll into 1 inch balls and brown and drain.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Toast desired bread and cut crosswise into triangle quarters for dipping (may trim bread crust).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and syrup in pan. Cook on low heat until it reaches soft-ball stage (234°). Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well and pour into an 8-inch buttered pie plate to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put cooked squash in baking dish; combine soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise and egg.
Pour mixture over squash.
