Combine crumbs and melted margarine and cheese; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave party dip
directions: Microwave on High for 7 minutes or until cheese melts, stirring every 2 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: pineapple crunch
directions: Put pineapple in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, cheese and pineapple juice.
Spread over pineapple.
Top with soaked crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flavoring.
Sift flour and soda together 3 times.
Stir in alternately with sour cream.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; cool.
Mix together graham crackers, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Place half of this mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Save half for top.
Cream together the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add jello that has been whipped just before it begins to set.
Whip the very cold Milnot.
Add to cream cheese/jello mixture and pour over crumb layer in pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: milk chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. In a large bowl, mix Cool Whip, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Stir in brownie mix just until moistened. Stir in nuts. Spread mixture into pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Do not overbake.
Cool and slice.

title: mashed potato fluff
directions: Fry ground beef and season.
Pour off grease and place in a loaf pan.
Cook and mash potatoes.
Spread potatoes over meat.
Cut cheese in half.
Place cheese in X on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chunky beef-barley soup
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
Brown meat and garlic in oil.
Drain. Add water, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, salt, basil and pepper. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Return to boil.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts of soup.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Toss the carrots, raisins and oranges together, moisten with mayonnaise and pile on mounds of shredded lettuce which has been moistened with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle shredded peanuts over salad. Serves six.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Drain all fruit thoroughly.
Combine sugar, flour and salt. Gradually stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice and cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture and cooked lecini depepe; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: eggs a la goldenrod
directions: Combine flour and shortening in saucepan.
Add milk and salt; cook over low heat until thickened.
Chop eggs and add to sauce. Spread on bread and bake in oven until bread is toasted.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: baked rhubarb(diabetic)
directions: Wash and cut rhubarb.
Grate orange peel, being careful to use only the colored part of the peel.
Mix all ingredients together and put them in a casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spanish delight casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger in skillet and cook.
Combine sauces and heat to boiling.
Warm Fritos and chili beans in 350° oven. Place chips in the bottom of a large casserole.
Then put hamburger over chips.
Add vegetables next, then chili beans and cheese.
Pour sauce over all.
Put together just before serving, then heat in oven several minutes.

title: cherry punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (don't salt) until tender.
Pick off bone and fat.
Set aside.
Save chicken broth.
Melt margarine and stir in dressing.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Mix the sugar, flour and milk in separate bowl. Add the cherries or other fruit. Don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: pink lemonade ice cream pie
directions: Mix quickly the ice cream and undiluted lemonade. Add color to reach shade desired and place in pie shells.
Cover and freeze. Top with Cool Whip and cherry when serving. Great for hurry up delicious light dessert for a group.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions, garlic and celery in olive oil.
Brown ground meat; add tomato sauce and paste.
Stir sauce until it comes to a hard boil.
Add as much water as tomato sauce and paste.
Bring to a boil again and then let it simmer until it is cooked.

title: chocolate orange eclairs
directions: Melt butter in water; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Immediately beat in flour and salt all at once.
Beat vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball, 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with mixer until smooth and glossy after each addition.
(Small amount of dough will stand erect when scooped on a spoon.)
Spoon 1/4 cupfuls into 4 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch "fingers," about 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until puffed and golden brown.
Prick sides with a fork; cool away from draft.
Cut off tops.
Remove soft dough from inside.
Fill each with 1/4 cup Chocolate Orange Custard.
Replace tops; frost with Chocolate Glaze.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in the bottom of a salad bowl.
Onions can be finely chopped or sliced and added.
Crush the onions with a fork after they are added and let them get soft.
Eggs are diced and added last.
Eggs must also be mashed with a fork after they are added to the mixture until the yolks become part of the liquid dressing.
Add greens; toss and enjoy!

title: party mix
directions: Mix oil and Hidden Valley Ranch in bowl; heat until warm in microwave.
Use 2 brown paper bags (double bag them); pour in all dry ingredients.
Pour oil mixture over and shake well.
Let it sit 2 to 3 hours and toss occasionally during that time.
Put M&M's in last.
Makes a lot.
Can be placed in Tupperware and frozen.

title: best ever rum cake
directions: Before starting, sample rum to check quality.
It should be smooth and not at all harsh to the palate.
Proceed.
Select large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is of proper quality, pour level cup of rum into glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure rum is still all ok right.
Try another cup.
Open second bottle i-fxx, ifff, if necessary.
Add eggs, 2 cups druit and beat until high.
If druit gets stuck in beeters, pry loose with drewscriber.
Sample rum again, checking for tonscisticity.
Next sift 3 cups pepper or sault, really doesn't matter.
Sample rum.
Sift 1/2 pint lemon juice.
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 bablespoon of brown thugar or whatever color you can find.
Wix mel.
Grease oven.
Turn cake pan to 350°.
Pour mess into boven and ake.
Check rum again and go to bed.

title: boiled drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, milk, cocoa and butter or margarine and bring to boil in double boiler, boil 15 minutes.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter; stir until blended.
Add oats and mix well. Add coconut or nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper and let stand at room temperature until firm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot chicken broth and line 9x13 pan or 2 small ones. On top of tortillas, put chicken, salta and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with garlic powder. Spread chopped onions and peppers on top of chicken. MIx both soups together and chili powder to taste. Then pour over the chicken, then put a layer of shredded cheese. Then spoon on mashed or blended Rotel tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 35 min.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.

Rinse macaroni and set aside. Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, butter, salt, pepper and shredded cheese; add macaroni and stir well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cabbage tsukemono
directions: Heat
hot water, brown sugar, salt and vinegar until it comes to a boil.	Cool.
Add the whiskey and pour the mixture over the cabbage.
Put into a container (such as a crock) that a
weight can be put on top of the cabbage.
It will be ready to
eat in two days.
Remove from the weight and put into jars or plastic container and refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Pour mixture into 5-quart freezer can and freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
In large bowl mix broccoli, soup, milk and cheese.
Pour in casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan. Pour cornbread mix over into butter.
Mix and spread over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans together.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Spread over the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Add beaten Dream Whip and spread over cooled pastry.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread cherry pie filling over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate again.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook milk, sugar and butter until it comes to a boil, then put in dates, chopped up.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cool water.
Take off and add the nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Don't beat.
Wet a clean cloth in cold water and wring dry.
Pour candy onto the cloth and form into a loaf.
Cut into slices when cool.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground beef, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Layer in baking dish the asparagus, peas, onion, soup and cheese.
Melt oleo.
Dip decrusted bread in oleo and place on top of dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
Combine with the beans.
Add remaining ingredients to taste.
Heat to boiling and serve.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, carrots and onions for 10 minutes.
Drain well. Add sour cream and soup, mix well and let sit for an hour on stove. Spread half of bread crumb mixture in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add squash mixture and top with remaining bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bundle meals(for the grill)
directions: For each meal you'll need a piece of foil wide enough and long enough to wrap around meat and vegetables.
Place in the middle of the foil in the order listed:
a hamburger patty, followed by the vegetables, a dab of margarine, salt and pepper.
Bring up one set of the sides of the foil and roll down to cover meal.
Then roll in the ends.
Seal seams well.
Grill over medium heat, meat side down first, 6 to 7 minutes.
Turn over and cook additional 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve in the foil.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Put a good amount of olive oil in the pot. Saute chopped onion and finely chopped garlic in olive oil. Add crushed tomatoes and water. (For a thicker sauce, add half the amount of water). Add chopped sun dried tomatoes. (Add more sun dried tomatoes for an even better flavor.)
Add salt, pepper, hot pepper and fresh basil. Simmer for about an hour and spread over your favorite pasta.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until firm.

title: anita's meatballs and gravy
directions: Roll all ingredients into balls.
Fast fry until brown.
Make gravy.
Add meat balls to gravy, almost cover with water and cook for 30 to 40 minutes, until gravy is cooked down and meat is done.

title: hamburger jalapeno pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add salt, pepper and onion. Drain and add all ingredients except cheese. Stir and pour into a large casserole dish. Cover with grated cheese. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted. Can be cooked in crock-pot on high. If cooked in crock-pot, take off cover last 20 minutes so it can set.

title: nut cheese ball
directions: Place all cheeses, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and garlic salt in bowl.
Attach bowl and flat beater.
Turn to speed 4 and beat until well blended.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with raw vegetables or assorted crackers.
Yields 1 (24 ounce) ball.

title: easy apple dessert
directions: Place apples in oblong dish.
Cut bread into thick slices and butter.
Place bread over apples, starting at end of dish and lapping one over other.
Add raisins.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Bake in uncooked deep pie shell at 350° until thick (nearly dry on top), about 40 to 45 minutes.
For best results, bake on cookie sheet.

title: chocolate milk
directions: Pour the milk in a glass.
Add chocolate syrup; mix and drink. Makes 1 serving.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini; slice lengthwise and scrape pulp out.
Chop zucchini meat; add onion and spaghetti sauce.
Put back into zucchini and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook until done, in covered skillet or in oven, about 15 minutes on medium heat.

title: quick and easy treat
directions: Take almond bark, break apart into bowl and put in microwave to melt.
While melting, take Ritz crackers, spread on peanut butter and top with another Ritz cracker, making a sandwich.
Make as many sandwiches as you would like.
Take peanut butter sandwiches and dip into melted chocolate.
Lay on wax paper to harden.
Quick and easy!
Very tasty, too!

title: lazy man's pie
directions: Heat peaches until hot.
Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart deep baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and water; pour into greased baking dish.
Pour hot peaches on top of mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Delicious on chicken and pork.

title: verna hoffman's easy german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Cool.
Ice with the icing recipe.

title: cranberry-horseradish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender (not the shrimp). Process until smooth.
Serve with cooked shrimp.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and peel and cut them up.
Cut up onion and eggs. Add salt and pepper.
Cut up bacon in small pieces and fry.
Use 1/2 of the bacon grease, then put all together in a bowl.
Add most of your bacon grease; add a little sugar.
Mix all together with your Miracle Whip.

title: monterey spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chilies.
Blend well. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. In small bowl, mix Ricotta and eggs.

title: homemade cake mix
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
With a pastry cutter, cut in shortening until resembles very coarse crumbs.
Put in a large airtight container.
Store in a cool dry place or in refrigerator.
Use within 10 to 12 weeks.

title: diabetic spiced pumpkin pie
directions: Beat pumpkin, evaporated milk and eggs in a medium bowl. Beat in remaining ingredients. Pour into
pastry shell. Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, approximately 40 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.

title: pea salad
directions: Chop onion and put in bowl.
Add sugar and set aside until you mix up the other things.
In another bowl, add lettuce (pinch up in small pieces).
Drain peas and put them in.
Cut up cheese and add it.
Add bacon bits and mayonnaise.
Then add onion and sugar. Stir up.
Put in bowl with a lid and set in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; pour over cut chicken wings. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: curly carrots
directions: You will need a mixing bowl, clean hands and round toothpicks.

title: cheese ball 1
directions: Grind cheese and walnuts together.
Blend in cream cheese, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Shape into a ball. Roll ball in chili powder and refrigerate until well chilled. Best made day before serving.
(May add a little salt to taste.)

title: molasses oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and molasses in bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and nutmeg in large bowl; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, walnuts and raisins; mix well.
Chill, covered, for several hours.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
54 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients into crumbs.
Slice apples into a greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup sugar; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put crumb mixture on top.
Pour melted butter on crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: joan's christmas bake
directions: Place bread cubes in shallow baking dish.
Top with cooked sausage (lumps broken up) and grated cheese.
For a special treat, make this with Cracker Barrel New York Cheddar.
This is a flexible recipe.
I have used as many as 10 to 12 eggs, more milk, etc., and up to 1 pound of sausage.
I think it tastes better with more cheese.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pie will form its own crust as it bakes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart dish and put in the refrigerator until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla. Spread over salad.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: beautiful fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of 2-quart double boiler or in saucepan set over hot water.
Meanwhile, sift together confectioners sugar and instant nonfat dry milk.

Stir Karo syrup, vanilla and water into chocolate butter mixture, then add sifted sugar-instant nonfat dry milk mixture one half at a time. Continue stirring until mixture is blended smooth, slightly shiny but thick enough to pile.
Remove from heat; add nuts.
Turn into buttered pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: buttermilk hot cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix with wire whisk.
Cook on hot griddle, turning over when bubbles appear.
Serve with your favorite syrup or topping. Serves 6.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix flour into sugar.
Add melted margarine.
Beat eggs and mix well with mixture.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together starting with butter, sugar and eggs, then rest of ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Dale's favorite!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; add milk.
Cook until thick; add small amount to beaten eggs, then return to pan.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.

title: cool cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least two hours.
Serve with bite size fresh vegetables.

title: broiled hot dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs lengthwise; do not cut in two.
Place cheese in slit.
Wrap bacon slice around hot dogs and fasten with a toothpick.
Place in broiler pan.
Quickly brown bacon on bottom side, turn and broil at medium heat until bacon is crisp.
Pour catsup over hot dogs a few minutes before ready to serve.

title: wild duck
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour into oven cooking bag and put in shallow pan (roasting pan).
Pour wine and orange juice into bag, mixing well with flour.
Brush duck with butter; sprinkle with salt, inside and out.
Place apple in cavity and put duck in bag.
Close bag with twist tie and make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top of bag.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
One duck, depending on size, will serve 1 to 2 people.
Serve with your favorite game sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare pastry shell.
Mix together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter or margarine, vanilla and salt until well blended.
(Use an electric mixer.)
Stir in pecans and pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 325° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Cool and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from bone; cut or tear into small thin strips.
Put chicken, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and sour cream into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Prepare stuffing according to directions on box.
Spread or drop stuffing on top of chicken mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes more.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat milk and lemonade together. Fold in Cool Whip. Put in shell and chill.

title: shrimp fandango
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add peppers and garlic and saute until peppers are tender, about 2 minutes. Increase heat to high.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring constantly, until shrimp begin to turn pink, about 2 minutes.
Add vermouth; continue to stir and cook until liquid is reduced, about 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated through.
If desired, serve over hot rice.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan (use shortening, not oil).
Combine ingredients; pour into tube pan and bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 25 minutes. Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This will make a 9-inch, 2 layer cake or 8-inch, 3 layer cake.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat all ingredients together, adding milk last.
Bake in crust for 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with fork until smooth.
Add other ingredients, except for 1/2 of the chopped nuts.
Mix together and form into a ball.
Roll in the remaining nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, pumpkin, spices and salt; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Beat in softened ice cream. Add pecans.
Spread in pastry shell; freeze until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream and pecan halves.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Rinse rice well; cook 1 cup wild rice in salted water until tender.
Cook celery and onions until almost tender with margarine.
Butter casserole dish and place rice, celery and onions in alternate layers until gone.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup on top.
Dot generously with margarine.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Bring to room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix jello and water until dissolved. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Keep refrigerated.
This can be put in a mold and decorate with strawberries or cranberries and pecans.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add slaw dressing sparingly at first.
Put into refrigerator 1 to 2 hours.
Add more slaw dressing before serving.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies.
Put Jell-O in mixing bowl; add water and then strawberries.
Blend and pour over Twinkies and chill about 15 minutes.
Mix cold milk and pudding mix as directed.
Spread over Twinkie mix.
Cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: rice and onion casserole
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Saute 1/2 cup uncooked rice until lightly browned.
Add 1/2 cup fresh or canned mushrooms.
Stir in 1 package of dried onion soup mix.
Add 1 cup of water.
Cook, covered, over low heat about 25 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix margarine, eggs, flour, sugar, vanilla and salt together. Add corn and milk.
Butter your baking dish.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour until firm. Stir after 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: In mixing bowl, add butter, beating on high speed until light and fluffy, continuing to beat gradually, adding sugar until mixed thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
(Secret to success is in the beating.)
After beating thoroughly reduce mixer to low or folding position.
Fold in flour until all has been added and blended thoroughly.
Add flavor to taste.
Bake in buttered and floured tube cake pan in oven at 300° for 45 minutes, increasing heat to 325°.
Total cooking time 1 hour or until brown.
Remove from oven, cool 15 minutes or more on cake rack.
Remove from pan, continue to cool.
Enjoy.

title: blueberry streusel muffins
directions: Combine flour with sugar and baking powder in large bowl.
Cut in butter until it is in tiny pieces.
Remove 3/4 cup of mixture to a small bowl.
Stir in cinnamon; reserve.
Combine milk with eggs and vanilla; add to flour mixture in large bowl.
Stir just until moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Spoon batter into butter or paper-lined muffin cups.
Sprinkle each with the reserved cinnamon/crumb mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Wrap each muffin individually in plastic wrap, then put all muffins together in foil to freeze.
They make a great "driving to work" breakfast.

title: egg white kisses
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add the brown sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Add the pecans.
Bake on a wet paper bag around 2-inches apart in a 250° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: custard and pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook over medium heat until thick.
Serve over sliced pound cake.

title: karen's carrots
directions: In a skillet, cook carrots in a small amount of water until almost tender.
Add ginger, sugar and margarine; heat over low heat until carrots are warm and coated with the sauce.
Sprinkle with the parsley.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Sprinkle rice over bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Should be single layer of chicken.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, bell pepper, beef and rice. Stir over high heat until browned.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Stir together; do not beat.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This cake stays very moist and needs no icing.

title: ice cream mountain
directions: Place ice cream in bowl then place other ingredients on top in any order.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Melt margarine.
Add stuffing mix, tossing to coat.
Stir in 3/4 cup stuffing mix into vegetable mixture.
Turn into ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° (until set).

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse and pat dry mushrooms.
Remove stems and brush caps with oil.
Place on buttered baking dish.
Combine crabmeat, egg, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and 1/2 cup of bread crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle over crab mixture. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 stuffed mushrooms.

title: neva's cranberry salad
directions: Wash and drain berries; run through food chopper.
Mix sugar and other ingredients.
Fold all together with jello and place in icebox.
Best to set overnight before serving.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Mix
first 5 ingredients together.
Slice rolls lengthwise. Spread
with
mixture on both sides.
Put ham in bottom half. Sprinkle
with cheese.
Close and wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix stuffing and margarine; set aside.
Mix together soups.
Layer stuffing mixture (enough to cover bottom), chicken and soup mixture.
Continue until ingredients are used up. End with stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: three cheese baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine
the
diced
rhubarb,
pineapple and sugar in a saucepan and allow to stand for 30 minutes.
Slowly bring to a boil;
reduce
heat
and
simmer for 12 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the strawberry gelatin and stir until dissolved. Fill
jelly
glasses
to
inch
from the top.	Cover with melted paraffin wax.

title: slippery slime(snack for halloween)
directions: Mix gelatin, jello and boiling water.
Pour into pan and let set in refrigerator.
Cut into worm shapes.
Decorate by adding red hot candy eyes.

title: sassafras root tea
directions: Wash roots and place in 2-quart granite pan.
Cover with boiling water and boil 20 minutes. Strain into a teapot.
Save the boiled roots for future brews.
Pass cream and sugar.

title: coleslaw
directions: Rinse cabbage.
Remove dark, tough outer leaves and shred. Core and cut pepper into thin rings.
Peel onion and cut into thin slices.
Cut cherry tomatoes in half lengthwise.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In medium pan, add cornstarch, sugar, salt, and cocoa.
Mix well. Add milk and stir well.
Add egg yolks.
Mix completely.
Cook over med heat, stirring constantly until mixture starts to thicken and boil.
Cook 1 minute more, stirring quickly.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly, pour into baked pie shell.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add 4 Tbsp sugar and beat until very stiff.
Spoon onto pie, making sure to touch edges with meringue.
Cool and serve cold.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan.
Put rhubarb in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb, then sprinkle dry jello on top of sugar. Spread marshmallows evenly over jello.
Mix cake as directed on package and pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, including the liquid in the kernel corn.
Bake in a Pam-sprayed 9 x 12-inch baking dish for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 people generously.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat and scramble eggs, parsley and nutmeg.
Cook just until almost done.
Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, eggs, sour cream, meat and cheese.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: slender french fries
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2-inch sticks.
Place sticks in a bowl of ice water to crisp.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Place potato sticks in a plastic bag.
Add cooking oil, paprika and salt. Shake to coat.
On a large baking sheet, arrange the potato sticks in a single layer. Bake in a 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden, turning once or twice. If desired, serve with catsup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into a slightly greased 2-quart casserole. Drizzle with butter. Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix soups together.
Cut tortillas in one-inch squares. Butter the dish, a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix onion with mixed soups and salsa.
Put in layers:
tortillas, chicken, soup mix and grated cheese.
Repeat.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, salt and paprika. Add remaining ingredients and toss well. Chill until ready to serve.

title: quick perlo
directions: Start cooking rice as usual.
In saucepan, brown 3 or 4 sausages and 1/2 pound bacon.
Add deboned chicken.
Put meat into rice; salt and pepper to taste.
You can add red peppers, if desired.

title: best-ever cube steak
directions: Brown butter and onion.
Remove onion.
Brown steak; return onion.
Add soup, water, and seasonings.
Cook slowly, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add sour cream to gravy.
Serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Cool.
Add all the above ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: turkey spinach enchilada casserole
directions: Prepare ahead.
Cook meat and onion in skillet; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, spinach and taco seasoning.
In bowl, combine soup, sour cream, milk and garlic powder.
Arrange 6 tortillas in 9 x 13-inch dish (cut to fit).
Spoon in meat mixture.
Spread chilies and 1 1/2 cups cheese over meat.
Cover with 6 tortillas, add soup mixture and smooth over.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle casserole with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with sour cream and hot sauce.
If ground beef is substituted, substitute cream of golden mushroom soup.

title: old fashioned hot milk cake
directions: Heat milk and butter together until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder.
Pour milk and butter mixture into this.
Add vanilla. May be used for cupcakes, sheet cake or 3 layer cake.

title: cookies
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until dissolved or about 3 minutes.
Mix all together and drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: easiest chocolate pie
directions: Pour pudding all together in pan; follow box direction less 1/2 cup milk.
When you have pudding, remove from stove.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon maple extract.
Add chopped nuts to taste.
Pour into pie crust and cool.
Then pile high with Cool Whip.
Good, good.

title: angel's artichoke dip
directions: Mix well in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with raw veggies, crackers, chips, etc.

title: brickle chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until like coarse meal.
Press firmly on ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat Eagle Brand milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Spread over crust.
Bake 25 minutes until done and golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: frito pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef.
Mix in the chile and onion.
In a large baking dish, put a small amount of chips on the bottom, then meat and cheese on top.
Repeat the layers until meat is gone.
Put cheese on the top and bake until chips are tender and cheese is melted.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter well.
Add brown sugar and blend well.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° on a greased cookie sheet.

title: oriental vegetable salad
directions: Boil the last 7 ingredients.
Mix all other ingredients (drained)
together
and
pour
the boiled (still hot) mixture over them.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, and beaten eggs. Add pumpkin and mix well, Combine dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Add water, beat thoroughly and pour into 2 greased 9x5x3 inch loaf pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: white chili
directions: Brown chicken chunks in olive oil for 10 minutes.
Add beans, salsa sauce, cumin and water.
Heat for 10 minutes.
Add grated cheese; stir until cheese is melted, about 7 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Divide into 3 greased bread pans. Bake at 250° to 325° depending on oven, about 1 hour.
(Should be moist but not sticky.)
Pecans may be added.
Freezes well.

title: memaw's shortbread
directions: You will need 1 large candle and large round platter.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon; dice, cool and crumble.
Brown hamburg in small amount of bacon grease with 1/2 chopped onion and drain.
In small roaster, mix all ingredients (including liquid in cans of beans). If it's too much liquid, drain either the can of butter beans or lima beans.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix the sweet potato, shortening and the milk together.
Add the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix with spoon and spoon in muffin tins.
Bake at about 400° or 375° for 18 minutes.

title: white frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar and Crisco in a medium sized bowl.
Slowly add vanilla and Parkay.
Add milk until desired thickness is achieved.
Add food coloring for decorating.

title: coconut pie(makes two pies)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, and cornstarch. Add melted butter, 4 egg yolks, and milk, stir until well mixed. Cook in microwave two minutes at a time until thick. Add vanilla and coconut. Pour into two baked pie shells. Top with meringue.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, baking powder and eggs. Add corn and mix.
Add sour cream; pinch of salt and pepper to taste and oil. Mix well. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in greased pan at 350°.

title: hot beef sandwich
directions: Roast beef 8 hours at 275°.
Cool and skim off fat; save juice.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice or break apart.
Mix into juice the au jus and salad dressing.
Pour over meat and reheat. Serve on buns.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream oleo and peanut butter.
Add other ingredients and roll in 1-inch balls.
Dip in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 minutes at 375°.
Press Hershey's Kiss in center of each cookie immediately upon removing from the oven.

title: sour cream brittle bread
directions: Mix yeast in 1 cup warm water and set aside.
Mix honey, 1 cup water and butter or margarine.
Add eggs, saving 1 egg white for later.
Mix in yeast solution.
Place flour in large bowl and form a depression in flour.
Add liquid and mix.
(More flour may be added if needed to get dough texture.)
Let rise in a warm room until double original size.
Dough may be divided into halves or fourths.
Knead dough into a rope shape, then braid or twist dough into loaves and place on baking sheet.
Brush on egg white and sprinkle sesame or poppy seed as desired.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix ingredients well; reserve 3/4 of butter and part of corn flakes for the top.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
